294
00:21:50,220 --> 00:21:53,020
<i>- Where's Atticus?
- [ Phone Ringing ]</i>

295
00:21:53,090 --> 00:21:57,490
<i>[ Dill ]
I can't see your daddy now either.</i>

296
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:02,430
<i>- I wonder where in the world--
- Scout, Jem.</i>

297
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,760
<i>What in the world
are you doing here?</i>

298
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,270
<i>[ Jem ]
Hello, Atticus.</i>

299
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:11,430
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

300
00:22:11,510 --> 00:22:15,100
<i>We came down to find out where
Boo Radley was locked up.</i>

301
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:18,110
<i>We wanted to see the bats.</i>

302
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:21,620
<i>I want you all
back home right away.</i>

303
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:24,120
<i>- Yes, sir.
- Run along now.</i>

304
00:22:24,190 --> 00:22:26,780
<i>I'll see you there for dinner.</i>

305
00:22:37,530 --> 00:22:40,560
<i>Hey, howdy, Cap'n.</i>

306
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:42,970
<i>Mr. Ewell.</i>

307
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:45,800
<i>Cap'n, I'm real sorry
they picked you...</i>

308
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:48,640
<i>to defend that nigger
that raped my Mayella.</i>

309
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:52,480
<i>I don't know why I didn't kill him
myself instead of going to the sheriff.</i>

310
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:55,880
<i>I'd have saved you and the sheriff
and the taxpayers lots of trouble.</i>

311
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:57,650
<i>Excuse me. I'm busy.</i>

312
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:02,590
<i>Hey, Cap'n, somebody told me
just now that they thought...</i>

313
00:23:02,660 --> 00:23:07,760
<i>that you believed Tom Robinson's story
agin ourn.</i>

314
00:23:07,830 --> 00:23:10,090
<i>You know what I said?</i>

315
00:23:10,170 --> 00:23:14,260
<i>[ Laughs ] I said,
"You're wrong, man. You're dead wrong!</i>

316
00:23:14,340 --> 00:23:18,270
