422
00:32:24,850 --> 00:32:26,790
<i>Time for bed.</i>

423
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:30,290
<i>Scout. Jem.</i>

424
00:32:48,510 --> 00:32:51,140
<i>[ Maudie ]
Morning.</i>

425
00:32:51,210 --> 00:32:53,150
<i>Good morning,
Miss Maudie.</i>

426
00:32:53,220 --> 00:32:55,150
<i>- Morning, Calpurnia.
- Morning, Maudie.</i>

427
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:57,310
<i>Came to see if Jean Louise is ready
for her first day of school.</i>

428
00:32:57,390 --> 00:32:59,320
<i>- [ Cal ] Scout!
- Good morning, Miss Maudie.</i>

429
00:32:59,390 --> 00:33:02,320
<i>- You ready too?
- Yes, ma'am.
- Scout!</i>

430
00:33:02,390 --> 00:33:05,690
<i>What are you gonna do yourself this morning,Calpurnia,
with both children at school?</i>

431
00:33:05,760 --> 00:33:09,250
<i>I don't know,
and that's the truth.</i>

432
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:11,930
<i>I was thinking
about that just now.</i>

433
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:13,940
<i>Scout!</i>

434
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:19,100
<i>Scout? Scout!</i>

435
00:33:19,170 --> 00:33:21,270
<i>Did you hear me, Scout?</i>

436
00:33:21,340 --> 00:33:23,280
<i>Now hurry.</i>

437
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:34,990
<i>[ Jem Laughs ]
Hey, look at Scout!</i>

438
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:36,620
<i>Shh.</i>

439
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,960
<i>- Come on in here, Scout.
- [ Stifling Laughter ]</i>

440
00:33:47,370 --> 00:33:50,300
<i>Have your breakfast.</i>

441
00:33:58,050 --> 00:34:00,980
<i>I think your dress
is mighty becomin', honey.</i>

442
00:34:01,050 --> 00:34:03,750
<i>[ Cal ] Don't go tugging
at that dress, Scout.</i>

443
00:34:03,820 --> 00:34:07,760
<i>You want to have it all wrinkled
before you even get to school?</i>

444
00:34:07,820 --> 00:34:12,350
<i>I still don't see why I have
to wear a darn old dress.</i>

445
00:34:12,430 --> 00:34:14,590
<i>- You'll get used to it.
- I'm ready!</i>

446
00:34:14,660 --> 00:34:18,100
<i>Oh, Jem. Jem.</i>

447
00:34:18,170 --> 00:34:22,260
<i>It's half an hour
before school starts.</i>

448
00:34:22,340 --> 00:34:25,770
<i>Sit right down
and wait for your sister.</i>

449
00:34:29,350 --> 00:34:33,980
<i>- Hurry up, Scout.
- I'm  trying to.</i>

450
00:34:34,050 --> 00:34:37,950
<i>[ Jem ] Come on! It's your first day.
You want to be late?</i>

451
00:34:39,860 --> 00:34:43,120
<i>- I'm ready.
- [ Jem ] Let's go!</i>

452
00:34:46,530 --> 00:34:48,460
<i>Bye.</i>

453
00:34:50,870 --> 00:34:52,800
<i>Bye, everybody!</i>

454
00:34:54,540 --> 00:34:56,800
<i>[ Chuckling ]</i>

455
00:34:56,870 --> 00:34:59,970
<i>[ Shouting ]</i>

456
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:10,420
<i>Darn you,
Walter Cunningham!</i>

457
00:35:10,490 --> 00:35:15,050
<i>[ Children Shouting ]</i>

458
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:18,250
<i>- [ Children ] Come on, Walter!
- Come on, Walter!</i>

459
00:35:18,330 --> 00:35:20,260
<i>- [ Jem ] Scout!
- Come on, Walter!</i>

460
00:35:20,330 --> 00:35:22,260
<i>Cut that out!</i>

461
00:35:22,330 --> 00:35:24,420
<i>What do you think you're doing?</i>

462
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:27,440
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

463
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:30,100
<i>He made me start off
on the wrong foot!</i>

464
00:35:30,170 --> 00:35:32,610
<i>I was trying to explain
to that darn lady teacher...</i>

465
00:35:32,670 --> 00:35:37,610
<i>why he didn't have no money
for his lunch, and she got sore at me!</i>

466
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:41,670
<i>Stop it! Stop it!</i>

467
00:35:48,790 --> 00:35:52,960
<i>Is your daddy Mr. Walter Cunningham
from Old Sarum?</i>

468
00:35:54,860 --> 00:35:56,960
<i>Come home and have dinner
with us, Walter.</i>

469
00:35:57,030 --> 00:35:59,130
<i>We'll be glad to have you.</i>

470
00:36:00,700 --> 00:36:03,900
<i>Our daddy is a friend
of your daddy's.</i>

471
00:36:03,970 --> 00:36:05,910
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

472
00:36:05,970 --> 00:36:09,070
<i>Scout here is crazy.
She won't fight you no more.</i>

473
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:15,580
<i>[ Atticus ]
I hope that's a dinner that you enjoy.</i>

474
00:36:15,650 --> 00:36:19,310
<i>Yes, sir. I don't know
when I've had a roast.</i>

475
00:36:19,390 --> 00:36:23,920
<i>We've been having squirrels
and rabbits lately.</i>

476
00:36:23,990 --> 00:36:28,760
<i>My pa and I go hunting
in our spare time.</i>

477
00:36:28,830 --> 00:36:32,430
<i>- You got a gun of your own?
- [ Walter ] Uh-huh.</i>

478
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:35,990
<i>- [ Jem ] How long you had a gun?
- Oh, a year or so.</i>

479
00:36:38,310 --> 00:36:41,110
<i>- Can I have the syrup, please?
- Certainly, son.</i>

480
00:36:41,180 --> 00:36:44,630
<i>Cal, will you bring in
the syrup dish, please?</i>

481
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:46,650
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

482
00:36:46,720 --> 00:36:48,980
<i>How old were you when you got
your first gun, Atticus?</i>

483
00:36:49,050 --> 00:36:52,280
<i>Thirteen or fourteen.</i>

484
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:58,150
<i>I remember when my daddy
gave me that gun.</i>

485
00:36:58,230 --> 00:37:02,130
<i>He told me that I should never point
at anything in the house...</i>

486
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:07,030
<i>and that he'd rather
I shoot at tin cans in the backyard.</i>

487
00:37:07,100 --> 00:37:09,400
<i>But he said that sooner
or later he supposed...</i>

488
00:37:09,470 --> 00:37:13,910
<i>the temptation to go after birds
would be too much...</i>

489
00:37:13,980 --> 00:37:19,570
<i>and that I could shoot all the blue jays
I wanted, if I could hit 'em;</i>

490
00:37:19,650 --> 00:37:23,050
<i>but to remember it was a sin
to kill a mockingbird.</i>

491
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:27,150
<i>- Why?
- [ Atticus ] Well, I reckon...</i>

492
00:37:27,220 --> 00:37:29,250
<i>because mockingbirds
don't do anything...</i>

493
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:33,450
<i>but make music
for us to enjoy.</i>

494
00:37:33,530 --> 00:37:36,090
<i>Don't eat people's gardens.</i>

495
00:37:36,160 --> 00:37:39,430
<i>Don't nest in the corn cribs.</i>

496
00:37:39,500 --> 00:37:43,940
<i>They don't do one thing but just
sing their hearts out for us.</i>

497
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:47,940
<i>How'd you like school, Scout?</i>

498
00:37:48,010 --> 00:37:50,950
<i>All right.</i>

499
00:37:51,010 --> 00:37:53,780
<i>Oh, thank you, Cal.
That's for Walter.</i>

500
00:38:14,840 --> 00:38:17,700
<i>- What in the Sam Hill
are you doing, Wa--
- [ Tapping ]</i>

501
00:38:17,770 --> 00:38:23,470
<i>But, Atticus, he's gone
and drowned his dinner in syrup,</i>

502
00:38:23,550 --> 00:38:26,040
<i>- and now he's pouring it all over--
- [ Cal ] Scout.</i>

503
00:38:26,110 --> 00:38:29,520
<i>- What?
- Come out here. I want to talk to you.</i>

504
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:40,290
<i>That boy is your company.</i>

505
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:43,960
<i>If he wants to eat that tablecloth,
you'll let him.</i>

506
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:46,130
<i>If you can't act fit
to eat like folks,</i>

507
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:48,800
<i>you can just sit here
and eat in the kitchen.</i>

508
00:38:51,670 --> 00:38:53,640
<i>[ Atticus ]
Scout.</i>

509
00:38:58,650 --> 00:39:00,640
<i>Scout.</i>

510
00:39:05,820 --> 00:39:09,660
<i>- [ Mumbling Softly ]
- Scout, what in the world
has got into you?</i>

511
00:39:09,730 --> 00:39:12,820
<i>- [ Repeating ] I'm not going back.
- Now, now.</i>

512
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:19,020
<i>Atticus, I'm not going back
to school anymore.</i>

513
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:21,500
<i>Now, Scout,
it's just the first day.</i>

514
00:39:21,570 --> 00:39:24,840
<i>I don't care.
Everything went wrong.</i>

515
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:27,500
<i>The teacher got mad
as the devil at me...</i>

516
00:39:27,580 --> 00:39:31,840
<i>and said you were teaching me
to read all wrong and to stop it,</i>

517
00:39:31,910 --> 00:39:35,820
<i>then acted like a fool and tried to give
Walter Cunningham a quarter...</i>

518
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:40,450
<i>when everybody knows Cunninghams
won't take nothin' from nobody.</i>

519
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:42,720
<i>Any fool could have told her that.</i>

520
00:39:42,790 --> 00:39:45,280
<i>Well... maybe she's just nervous.</i>

521
00:39:45,360 --> 00:39:49,460
<i>After all, it's her first day
teaching school and being new here.</i>

522
00:39:49,530 --> 00:39:53,800
<i>- Oh, Atticus--
- Now, wait a minute.</i>

523
00:39:55,870 --> 00:39:58,140
<i>If you learn
this single trick, Scout,</i>

524
00:39:58,210 --> 00:40:01,300
<i>you'll get along a lot better
with all kinds of folks.</i>

525
00:40:01,380 --> 00:40:03,640
<i>You never really
understand a person...</i>

526
00:40:03,710 --> 00:40:07,080
<i>until you consider things
from his point of view.</i>

527
00:40:07,150 --> 00:40:08,640
<i>Sir?</i>

528
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:12,980
<i>Until you climb inside of his skin
and walk around in it.</i>

529
00:40:13,060 --> 00:40:18,320
<i>But if I keep going to school,
we can't ever read anymore.</i>

530
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,990
<i>Scout...</i>

531
00:40:24,070 --> 00:40:27,830
<i>do you know what
a compromise is?</i>

532
00:40:27,900 --> 00:40:30,670
<i>Bending the law?</i>

533
00:40:32,410 --> 00:40:35,100
<i>Uh... no.</i>

534
00:40:35,180 --> 00:40:39,270
<i>It's an agreement reached
by mutual consent.</i>

535
00:40:39,350 --> 00:40:43,580
<i>Now... here's
the way it works.</i>

536
00:40:46,350 --> 00:40:51,290
<i>You concede the necessity
of going to school,</i>

537
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:55,300
<i>we'll keep right on reading
the same every night...</i>

538
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:58,130
<i>just as we always have.</i>

539
00:40:59,870 --> 00:41:01,800
<i>That a bargain?</i>

540
00:41:05,110 --> 00:41:07,940
<i>[ Adult Scout Narrating ]
There just didn't seem to be...</i>

541
00:41:08,010 --> 00:41:12,140
<i>anyone or anything
Atticus couldn't explain.</i>

542
00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:15,980
<i>Though it wasn't a talent
that would arouse the admiration
of any of our friends,</i>

543
00:41:16,050 --> 00:41:19,150
<i>Jem and I had to admit
he was very good at that.</i>

544
00:41:19,220 --> 00:41:24,320
<i>- [ Dog Growling ]
- But that was all
he was good at... we thought.</i>

545
00:41:24,390 --> 00:41:27,730
<i>- See? There he is.
- [ Growling Continues ]</i>

546
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:30,290
<i>[ Snarling, Growling ]</i>

547
00:41:30,370 --> 00:41:33,300
<i>[ Snarling, Growling Continue ]</i>

548
00:41:36,910 --> 00:41:39,930
<i>Scout, Jem,
come on inside.</i>

549
00:41:40,010 --> 00:41:42,940
<i>- [ Snarling Continues ]
- Come on! Come on. Get in.</i>

550
00:41:51,190 --> 00:41:53,420
<i>Mr. Finch?
This is Cal.</i>

551
00:41:53,490 --> 00:41:56,360
<i>I swear to God, there's a mad dog
down the street a piece.</i>

552
00:41:56,420 --> 00:41:58,360
<i>He's coming this way!</i>

553
00:41:58,430 --> 00:42:04,130
<i>[ Car Approaching ]</i>

554
00:42:05,870 --> 00:42:08,730
<i>There he is.</i>

555
00:42:11,770 --> 00:42:13,970
<i>He's got it, all right,
Mr. Finch.</i>

556
00:42:17,210 --> 00:42:19,980
<i>Stay inside, son.
Keep them in there, Cal.</i>

557
00:42:21,220 --> 00:42:23,620
<i>He's within range, Heck.</i>

558
00:42:23,690 --> 00:42:26,480
<i>- [ Dog Snarling ]
- Take him, Mr. Finch.</i>

559
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:30,320
<i>- Oh, no, Mr. Tate! He can't shoot!
- Don't waste time, Heck.</i>

560
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:33,990
<i>He's got to be killed
before he starts runnin'.</i>

561
00:42:34,060 --> 00:42:36,590
<i>Look where he is. I can't shoot
that well, and you know it.</i>

562
00:42:36,670 --> 00:42:38,690
<i>[ Atticus ]
I haven't shot a gun in years.</i>

563
00:42:38,770 --> 00:42:41,760
<i>I'd feel mighty comfortable
if you did now.</i>

564
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:47,470
<i>[ Dog Snarling, Barking ]</i>

565
00:42:47,540 --> 00:42:50,640
<i>[ Snarling, Barking Continue ]</i>

566
00:42:50,710 --> 00:42:54,050
<i>[ Growling ]</i>

567
00:43:06,490 --> 00:43:10,950
<i>[ Growling Continues ]</i>

568
00:43:34,820 --> 00:43:39,920
<i>- Don't go near that dog. He's just
as dangerous dead as alive.
- Yes, sir.</i>

569
00:43:41,660 --> 00:43:44,760
<i>- Atticus?
- Yes, son.</i>

570
00:43:47,500 --> 00:43:51,440
<i>- Nothin'.
- What's the matter, boy?
Can't you talk?</i>

571
00:43:51,510 --> 00:43:55,310
<i>- Didn't you know your daddy is
the best shot in this county?
- Oh, hush, Heck.</i>

572
00:43:55,380 --> 00:43:57,440
<i>Let's get back to town.</i>

573
00:43:57,510 --> 00:44:01,610
<i>- Remember now, don't go near that dog.
- Yes, sir.</i>

574
00:44:01,680 --> 00:44:04,950
<i>I'll send Zeebo out right away
to pick him up.</i>

575
00:44:24,570 --> 00:44:27,300
<i>[ Jem Shouts ]
Hey, Atticus, can we go with ya?</i>

576
00:44:28,580 --> 00:44:30,770
<i>- Can we, please?
- Huh, can we?</i>

577
00:44:30,850 --> 00:44:33,780
<i>I have to go to the country on business,
and you'll just get tired.</i>

578
00:44:33,850 --> 00:44:36,840
<i>Oh, no, not me.
I won't get tired.</i>

579
00:44:36,920 --> 00:44:41,180
<i>Well, you promise to stay in the car
while I talk to Helen Robinson?</i>

580
00:44:41,260 --> 00:44:44,350
<i>- Mm-hmm.
- And not nag me about leaving
if you get tired?</i>

581
00:44:44,430 --> 00:44:46,520
<i>- Huh-uh.
- All right, climb in.</i>

582
00:44:54,740 --> 00:44:59,400
<i>- Who's Helen Robinson?
- She's the wife of the man
I'm defending.</i>

583
00:45:03,910 --> 00:45:05,850
<i>[ Brakes Squeak ]</i>

584
00:45:18,730 --> 00:45:21,530
<i>- Good evening, David.
- Good evening.</i>

585
00:45:21,600 --> 00:45:24,190
<i>- Good evening, Helen.
- Evening, Mr. Finch.</i>

586
00:45:24,270 --> 00:45:27,430
<i>- I came over to tell you
about my visit with Tom.
- Yes, sir.</i>

587
00:45:27,500 --> 00:45:29,830
<i>And to let you know
that I got a postponement of the trial.</i>

588
00:45:29,900 --> 00:45:33,310
<i>[ Atticus Continues, lndistinct ]</i>

589
00:45:50,330 --> 00:45:54,390
<i>[ Leaves Rustling ]</i>

590
00:46:04,170 --> 00:46:07,270
<i>Would you tell my daddy
to come out here, please?</i>

591
00:46:30,500 --> 00:46:33,020
<i>[ Footsteps Approaching ]</i>

592
00:46:56,860 --> 00:46:59,830
<i>You nigger lover.</i>

593
00:47:17,250 --> 00:47:20,840
<i>No need to be afraid of him, son.
He's all bluff.</i>

594
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:24,280
<i>[ Starts Engine ]</i>

595
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,530
<i>[ Ewell ]
Nigger lover!</i>

596
00:47:49,310 --> 00:47:54,270
<i>There's a lot of ugly things
in this world, son.</i>

597
00:47:54,350 --> 00:47:57,280
<i>I wish I could
keep 'em all away from you.</i>

598
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:03,250
<i>That's never possible.</i>

599
00:48:03,320 --> 00:48:07,320
<i>Cal, if you wait 'til I get Scout
in bed, I'll drive you home.</i>

600
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:09,330
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

601
00:48:22,980 --> 00:48:27,180
<i>Jem, do you mind stayin' here with Scout
'til I get Cal home?</i>

602
00:48:27,250 --> 00:48:29,880
<i>- No, sir.
- Night, Jem.</i>

603
00:48:29,950 --> 00:48:33,390
<i>Night, Cal.</i>

604
00:48:33,450 --> 00:48:35,390
<i>[ Car Door Shuts ]</i>

605
00:48:40,330 --> 00:48:43,560
<i>[ Engine Starts, Car Departs ]</i>

606
00:48:43,630 --> 00:48:45,570
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

607
00:48:57,110 --> 00:49:01,170
<i>[ Rustling Continues ]</i>

608
00:49:01,250 --> 00:49:05,520
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

609
00:49:05,590 --> 00:49:10,850
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

610
00:49:10,930 --> 00:49:14,330
<i>[ Rustling Continues ]</i>

611
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:18,700
<i>[ Bird Screeching ]</i>

612
00:49:18,770 --> 00:49:22,760
<i>Atticus! Atticus!</i>

613
00:49:22,840 --> 00:49:24,770
<i>Atticus!</i>

614
00:49:31,080 --> 00:49:33,140
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>

615
00:49:33,210 --> 00:49:36,150
<i>[ Bird Screeches ]</i>

616
00:49:38,150 --> 00:49:42,320
<i>[ Banging, Creaking ]</i>

617
00:49:42,390 --> 00:49:45,330
<i>[ Banging, Creaking Continue ]</i>

618
00:49:52,530 --> 00:49:57,230
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>

619
00:49:57,310 --> 00:49:59,740
<i>[ Banging, Creaking ]</i>

620
00:49:59,810 --> 00:50:03,740
<i>[ Continues Banging, Creaking ]</i>

621
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:13,980
<i>[ Bird Screeches ]</i>

622
00:50:36,580 --> 00:50:39,050
<i>[ Banging ]</i>

623
00:50:39,110 --> 00:50:41,810
<i>[ Banging, Creaking ]</i>

624
00:50:41,880 --> 00:50:44,350
<i>[ Banging Continues ]</i>

625
00:50:48,860 --> 00:50:51,590
<i>[ Banging Continues ]</i>

626
00:50:51,660 --> 00:50:54,220
<i>[ Bird Screeches ]</i>

627
00:51:02,740 --> 00:51:05,760
<i>[ Adult Scout ]
Atticus had promised me
he would wear me out...</i>

628
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:08,500
<i>if he ever heard
of me fightin' anymore.</i>

629
00:51:08,580 --> 00:51:12,170
<i>I was far too old and too big
for such childish things.</i>

630
00:51:12,250 --> 00:51:17,580
<i>And the sooner I learned to hold in,
the better off everybody would be.</i>

631
00:51:17,650 --> 00:51:20,590
<i>I soon forgot.</i>

632
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:24,060
<i>Cecil Jacobs made me forget.</i>

633
00:51:26,930 --> 00:51:29,860
<i>Oh, what is it, Scout?</i>

634
00:51:33,430 --> 00:51:35,660
<i>Atticus, do you defend niggers?</i>

635
00:51:39,070 --> 00:51:41,910
<i>- Don't say "nigger," Scout.
- I didn't say it.</i>

636
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:45,340
<i>Cecil Jacobs did.
That's why I had to fight him.</i>

637
00:51:45,410 --> 00:51:48,350
<i>Scout,
I don't want you fightin'.</i>

638
00:51:48,420 --> 00:51:50,780
<i>I had to, Atticus.</i>

639
00:51:50,850 --> 00:51:53,840
<i>- He--
- I don't care what the reasons are.</i>

640
00:51:53,920 --> 00:51:58,190
<i>- I forbid you to fight.
- Yes.</i>

641
00:52:03,600 --> 00:52:09,130
<i>Anyway... I'm simply defending
a Negro, Tom Robinson.</i>

642
00:52:10,540 --> 00:52:13,300
<i>Now, Scout,
there are some things that...</i>

643
00:52:13,370 --> 00:52:17,310
<i>you're not old enough
to understand just yet.</i>

644
00:52:19,050 --> 00:52:23,980
<i>There's been some high talk
around town...</i>

645
00:52:24,050 --> 00:52:28,150
<i>to the effect that I shouldn't do much
about defending this man.</i>

646
00:52:30,390 --> 00:52:35,090
<i>If you shouldn't be defending him,
then why are you doing it?</i>

647
00:52:40,230 --> 00:52:43,930
<i>For a number of reasons.</i>

648
00:52:44,010 --> 00:52:46,700
<i>The main one is that,
if I didn't,</i>

649
00:52:46,770 --> 00:52:50,610
<i>I couldn't hold
my head up in town.</i>

650
00:52:50,680 --> 00:52:53,670
<i>I couldn't even tell you or Jem...</i>

651
00:52:53,750 --> 00:52:56,680
<i>not to do something again.</i>

652
00:52:59,450 --> 00:53:01,390
<i>[ Softly ]
Scout.</i>

653
00:53:04,130 --> 00:53:08,190
<i>You're gonna hear some
ugly talk about this in school.</i>

654
00:53:08,260 --> 00:53:12,720
<i>But I want you
to promise me one thing:</i>

655
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:15,770
<i>That you won't get
into fights over it,</i>

656
00:53:15,840 --> 00:53:18,970
<i>no matter what
they say to you.</i>

657
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:26,580
<i>- [ Car Approaching ]
- Yes, sir.</i>

658
00:53:36,220 --> 00:53:38,660
<i>[ Car Engine ldling ]</i>

659
00:53:40,860 --> 00:53:44,530
<i>- What are you doing?
- I'm walking like an Egyptian.</i>

660
00:53:44,600 --> 00:53:47,470
<i>- We were studyin' about 'em in school.
- [ Engine Stops ]</i>

661
00:53:47,540 --> 00:53:49,730
<i>Teacher says we wouldn't
be no place without 'em.</i>

662
00:53:49,800 --> 00:53:51,900
<i>Is that so?</i>

663
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:56,270
<i>Cradle of civilization. They invented
embalming and toilet paper.</i>

664
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:01,140
<i>That's wrong, Scout.</i>

665
00:54:04,090 --> 00:54:09,150
<i>- You do your feet this way.
- Look, Jem.</i>

666
00:54:24,510 --> 00:54:29,340
<i>Look, the boy wears hair
in front of his eyebrows like you do.</i>

667
00:54:29,410 --> 00:54:32,740
<i>Yeah, and the girl
wears bangs like you.</i>

668
00:54:32,810 --> 00:54:35,250
<i>[ Whispers ]
These are of us.</i>

669
00:55:07,650 --> 00:55:10,710
<i>[ Children Running ]</i>

670
00:55:30,200 --> 00:55:32,140
<i>[ Softly ]
Jem, you awake?</i>

671
00:55:32,210 --> 00:55:35,770
<i>- Go back to bed.
- I can't go to sleep.</i>

672
00:55:35,840 --> 00:55:38,310
<i>Go back to bed.</i>

673
00:55:38,380 --> 00:55:40,310
<i>[ Scout ]
What you got in the box?</i>

674
00:55:40,380 --> 00:55:42,410
<i>Nothin'. Go back to bed.</i>

675
00:55:50,760 --> 00:55:52,690
<i>Come on.</i>

676
00:56:00,000 --> 00:56:03,030
<i>If I show you, will you swear
never to tell anybody?</i>

677
00:56:03,100 --> 00:56:05,540
<i>I swear.</i>

678
00:56:05,610 --> 00:56:07,600
<i>Cross your heart.</i>

679
00:56:19,220 --> 00:56:24,820
<i>[ Watch Ticking ]</i>

680
00:56:24,890 --> 00:56:29,300
<i>[ Ticking Continues ]</i>

681
00:56:29,360 --> 00:56:31,920
<i>- [ Ticking ]
- [ Jem ] I found all of these...</i>

682
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:35,090
<i>in the knothole of that old tree
at different times.</i>

683
00:56:37,440 --> 00:56:39,370
<i>[ Softly ]
This is a spelling medal.</i>

684
00:56:42,510 --> 00:56:45,310
<i>You know they used to award these
in school to spelling winners...</i>

685
00:56:45,380 --> 00:56:47,750
<i>before we were born.</i>

686
00:56:48,950 --> 00:56:52,650
<i>And another time,
I found this.</i>

687
00:56:52,720 --> 00:56:57,490
<i>[ Ticking ]</i>

688
00:56:57,560 --> 00:57:01,290
<i>[ Ticking Continues ]</i>

689
00:57:06,670 --> 00:57:08,600
<i>And this.</i>

690
00:57:21,830 --> 00:57:25,360
<i>Scout...</i>

691
00:57:25,430 --> 00:57:29,270
<i>you know somethin' else I never told you
about that night I went back...</i>

692
00:57:29,340 --> 00:57:31,360
<i>- to the Radley house?
- "Somethin' else"?</i>

693
00:57:31,440 --> 00:57:34,030
<i>You never told me anything
about that night.</i>

694
00:57:34,110 --> 00:57:37,140
<i>Well...</i>

695
00:57:37,210 --> 00:57:40,050
<i>the first time when I was
gettin' out of my britches?</i>

696
00:57:40,120 --> 00:57:43,710
<i>- Uh-huh.
- Well, they was all in a tangle,</i>

697
00:57:43,790 --> 00:57:47,190
<i>and I couldn't get 'em loose.</i>

698
00:57:47,260 --> 00:57:51,390
<i>Well, when I went back, though,</i>

699
00:57:51,460 --> 00:57:54,900
<i>they were folded
across the fence,</i>

700
00:57:54,960 --> 00:57:57,300
<i>sort of like
they was expectin' me.</i>

701
00:58:02,300 --> 00:58:04,770
<i>[ Watch Ticking ]</i>

702
00:58:04,840 --> 00:58:07,670
<i>[ Adult Scout ]
It was to be a long time...</i>

703
00:58:07,740 --> 00:58:11,080
<i>before Jem and I talked
about Boo again.</i>

704
00:58:16,280 --> 00:58:19,340
<i>School finally ended
and summer came...</i>

705
00:58:19,420 --> 00:58:21,790
<i>and so did Dill.</i>

706
00:58:21,860 --> 00:58:25,310
<i>- Good mornin'.
- Good mornin'. My, you're up...</i>

707
00:58:25,390 --> 00:58:26,980
<i>mighty bright and early.</i>

708
00:58:27,060 --> 00:58:28,820
<i>Ooh, I been up since 4:00.</i>

709
00:58:28,900 --> 00:58:32,830
<i>- [ Cal ] 4:00?
- Oh, yes, I always get up at 4:00.</i>

710
00:58:32,900 --> 00:58:34,830
<i>It's in my blood.</i>

711
00:58:34,900 --> 00:58:38,340
<i>You see,my daddy was a railroad man
'til he got rich.</i>

712
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:39,960
<i>Now he flies airplanes.</i>

713
00:58:40,040 --> 00:58:41,530
<i>One of these days,</i>

714
00:58:41,610 --> 00:58:43,700
<i>he's just gonna swoop
down here at Maycomb,</i>

715
00:58:43,780 --> 00:58:46,040
<i>pick me up and take me
for a ride.</i>

716
00:58:54,650 --> 00:58:57,710
<i>Who's that in the car
with Sheriff Tate?</i>

717
00:58:57,790 --> 00:59:00,490
<i>Tom Robinson, son.</i>

718
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:02,490
<i>Where's he been?</i>

719
00:59:02,560 --> 00:59:05,860
<i>In the Abbottsville jail.</i>

720
00:59:05,930 --> 00:59:09,870
<i>- Why?
- The sheriff thought
he'd be safer there.</i>

721
00:59:09,940 --> 00:59:12,530
<i>They're bringin' him
back here tonight...</i>

722
00:59:12,610 --> 00:59:14,900
<i>because his trial
is tomorrow.</i>

723
00:59:24,250 --> 00:59:27,710
<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>

724
00:59:27,790 --> 00:59:29,880
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>

725
00:59:32,390 --> 00:59:35,760
<i>- Well, good evenin', Heck.
- Good evenin', Mr. Finch.</i>

726
00:59:36,900 --> 00:59:38,830
<i>Come in.</i>

727
00:59:42,900 --> 00:59:47,900
<i>The news has gotten around
the county about my bringin'
Tom Robinson back to the jail.</i>

728
00:59:47,970 --> 00:59:52,810
<i>I, uh, heard there might be trouble
from that bunch out at Old Sarum.</i>

729
01:00:01,250 --> 01:00:05,850
<i>Cal, if I need you to stay here tonight,
can you do it?</i>

730
01:00:05,930 --> 01:00:08,420
<i>- Yes, sir, I can.
- Thank you.</i>

731
01:00:11,060 --> 01:00:13,500
<i>[ Dishes Clattering ]</i>

732
01:00:15,200 --> 01:00:17,140
<i>I think you better
count on stayin'.</i>

733
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:19,830
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

734
01:00:39,930 --> 01:00:44,120
<i>[ Door Opens, Shuts ]</i>

735
01:00:45,830 --> 01:00:49,670
<i>[ Car Door Opens, Shuts ]</i>

736
01:00:49,740 --> 01:00:54,000
<i>[ Engine Starts,
Car Departs ]</i>

737
01:00:54,070 --> 01:00:57,010
<i>- What's goin' on?
- Shh. Go back to sleep.</i>

738
01:00:57,080 --> 01:01:00,510
<i>- [ Scout ] What's goin' on?
- Shh.</i>

739
01:01:09,160 --> 01:01:11,590
<i>[ Jem Whispers ]
Hey, there's his car.</i>

740
01:01:23,500 --> 01:01:26,870
<i>[ Whispering ]
There he is over there.</i>

741
01:01:29,480 --> 01:01:33,570
<i>No, Scout, don't go to him.
He might not like it.</i>

742
01:01:33,650 --> 01:01:39,180
<i>I just wanted to see where he was
and what he was up to.</i>

743
01:01:39,250 --> 01:01:41,690
<i>He's all right.
Let's go back home.</i>

744
01:01:41,750 --> 01:01:43,690
<i>Come on.</i>

745
01:01:44,820 --> 01:01:46,760
<i>[ Cars Approaching ]</i>

746
01:01:50,730 --> 01:01:53,160
<i>[ Cars Approaching ]</i>

747
01:02:15,990 --> 01:02:19,480
<i>[ Brakes Squeaking ]</i>

748
01:02:21,390 --> 01:02:23,330
<i>[ Engines Stop ]</i>

749
01:02:41,350 --> 01:02:45,580
<i>- He in there, Mr. Finch?
- He is.</i>

750
01:02:45,650 --> 01:02:49,140
<i>He's asleep.
Don't wake him.</i>

751
01:02:49,220 --> 01:02:51,990
<i>You know what we want.</i>

752
01:02:53,930 --> 01:02:57,050
<i>Get aside from that door,
Mr. Finch.</i>

753
01:02:59,230 --> 01:03:01,170
<i>Walter...</i>

754
01:03:03,170 --> 01:03:06,610
<i>I think you oughta turn
right around and go back home.</i>

755
01:03:06,670 --> 01:03:10,470
<i>- Heck Tate's around here somewhere.
- [ Man ] No, he ain't!</i>

756
01:03:10,540 --> 01:03:13,740
<i>Heck and his bunch is out in Old Sarum,
lookin' for us.</i>

757
01:03:13,810 --> 01:03:16,210
<i>[ Man #2 ] We knowed he was,
so we come in this other way.</i>

758
01:03:16,280 --> 01:03:20,180
<i>- You ain't thought
about that, had you, Mr. Finch?
- [ Atticus ] I thought about it.</i>

759
01:03:20,250 --> 01:03:25,190
<i>- I can't see Atticus.
- [ Atticus ]
Well, that changes things some.</i>

760
01:03:25,260 --> 01:03:28,690
<i>[ Scout ]
Atticus.</i>

761
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:33,520
<i>- Hey, Atticus.
- Jem, go home.</i>

762
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:37,760
<i>Take Scout and Dill
home with you.</i>

763
01:03:37,840 --> 01:03:41,270
<i>- Son, I said go home.
- No, sir.</i>

764
01:03:43,440 --> 01:03:45,470
<i>- I'll send him home.
- Don't you touch him!</i>

765
01:03:45,550 --> 01:03:47,600
<i>Let him go!
Let him go!</i>

766
01:03:47,680 --> 01:03:49,610
<i>That'll do, Scout.</i>

767
01:03:52,490 --> 01:03:55,550
<i>Ain't nobody gonna
do Jem that way!</i>

768
01:03:56,720 --> 01:03:58,690
<i>You get 'em out of here,
Mr. Finch.</i>

769
01:04:03,330 --> 01:04:06,490
<i>Jem, I want you to please leave.</i>

770
01:04:06,570 --> 01:04:08,900
<i>- No, sir.
- Jem!</i>

771
01:04:08,970 --> 01:04:12,270
<i>I tell you, I ain't goin'.</i>

772
01:04:12,340 --> 01:04:14,270
<i>Hey, Mr. Cunningham.</i>

773
01:04:16,940 --> 01:04:22,250
<i>I said, "Hey, Mr. Cunningham."
How's your entailment gettin' along?</i>

774
01:04:23,550 --> 01:04:28,080
<i>Don't you remember me,
Mr. Cunningham?</i>

775
01:04:28,150 --> 01:04:32,890
<i>I'm Jean Louise Finch.</i>

776
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:37,160
<i>You brought us some hickory nuts
one morning. Remember?</i>

777
01:04:37,230 --> 01:04:40,430
<i>We had a talk.</i>

778
01:04:40,500 --> 01:04:44,660
<i>I went and got my daddy
to come out and thank you.</i>

779
01:04:44,740 --> 01:04:49,040
<i>I go to school with your boy.
I go to school with Walter.</i>

780
01:04:49,110 --> 01:04:51,340
<i>He's a nice boy.</i>

781
01:04:51,410 --> 01:04:53,900
<i>Tell him "hey" for me,
won't you?</i>

782
01:04:53,980 --> 01:04:57,070
<i>You know somethin',
Mr. Cunningham?</i>

783
01:04:57,150 --> 01:04:59,140
<i>Entailments are bad.</i>

784
01:04:59,220 --> 01:05:02,480
<i>- Entailments--
- [ Men Shuffling ]</i>

785
01:05:04,120 --> 01:05:06,790
<i>[ Coughing ]</i>

786
01:05:08,690 --> 01:05:13,690
<i>Atticus, I was just sayin'
to Mr. Cunningham
that entailments were bad,</i>

787
01:05:13,770 --> 01:05:15,960
<i>but not to worry.</i>

788
01:05:16,040 --> 01:05:18,630
<i>It takes a long time sometimes.</i>

789
01:05:20,340 --> 01:05:22,270
<i>What's the matter?</i>

790
01:05:30,480 --> 01:05:34,150
<i>I sure meant no harm,
Mr. Cunningham.</i>

791
01:05:37,920 --> 01:05:41,050
<i>No harm taken, young lady.</i>

792
01:05:43,730 --> 01:05:45,660
<i>I'll tell Walter
you said, "Hey."</i>

793
01:05:46,870 --> 01:05:48,990
<i>Let's clear outta here.</i>

794
01:05:50,500 --> 01:05:53,270
<i>Let's go, boys.</i>

795
01:05:53,340 --> 01:05:57,610
<i>[ Men Murmuring ]</i>

796
01:06:03,480 --> 01:06:05,780
<i>[ Engines Starting ]</i>

797
01:06:05,850 --> 01:06:09,790
<i>[ Engines Revvng ]</i>

798
01:06:16,230 --> 01:06:20,960
<i>- [ Cars Departing ]
- Now you can go home.</i>

799
01:06:21,030 --> 01:06:23,520
<i>All of you.</i>

800
01:06:23,600 --> 01:06:25,870
<i>I'll be there later.</i>

801
01:06:27,510 --> 01:06:29,910
<i>Come on.</i>

802
01:06:29,980 --> 01:06:31,910
<i>Come on.</i>

803
01:06:56,400 --> 01:07:01,310
<i>[ Tom Whispers ]
Mr. Finch, are they gone?</i>

804
01:07:01,370 --> 01:07:05,740
<i>They've gone.
They won't bother you anymore.</i>

805
01:07:26,070 --> 01:07:28,000
<i>[ Jem ]
'Morning, Mr. Strikes.</i>

806
01:07:28,070 --> 01:07:30,830
<i>- How do you do?
- Ever seen so many people?</i>

807
01:07:30,900 --> 01:07:33,370
<i>Just like on Saturday.</i>

808
01:07:35,210 --> 01:07:37,140
<i>Where you goin'?</i>

809
01:07:37,210 --> 01:07:40,740
<i>I can't stand it any longer.
I'm goin' to the courthouse and watch.</i>

810
01:07:40,810 --> 01:07:44,510
<i>- You better not.
You know what Atticus said.
- I don't care if he did.</i>

811
01:07:44,580 --> 01:07:48,350
<i>I'm not gonna miss
the most exciting thing that
ever happened in this town.</i>

812
01:08:05,370 --> 01:08:07,810
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

813
01:08:07,870 --> 01:08:11,810
<i>It's packed solid.
They're standin' all along the back.</i>

814
01:08:13,310 --> 01:08:15,870
<i>- Reverend.
- Yes?</i>

815
01:08:15,950 --> 01:08:20,080
<i>- Reverend Sykes,
are you going upstairs?
- Yes, I am.</i>

816
01:08:20,150 --> 01:08:23,090
<i>[ Crowd Chattering ]</i>

817
01:08:27,230 --> 01:08:29,790
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

818
01:08:29,860 --> 01:08:33,200
<i>- Thank you, Brother John,
for holding my seat.
- That's okay, Reverend.</i>

819
01:08:33,270 --> 01:08:36,500
<i>Come on, children.
Come on, come on.</i>

820
01:08:36,570 --> 01:08:40,510
<i>[ Baby Crying ]</i>

821
01:08:40,570 --> 01:08:43,630
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

822
01:08:43,710 --> 01:08:47,650
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

823
01:09:01,890 --> 01:09:05,800
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

824
01:09:10,170 --> 01:09:13,160
<i>[ Clerk ]
This court's now in session.
Everybody rise.</i>

825
01:09:17,540 --> 01:09:21,710
<i>- [ Gavel Pounding ]
- [ Crowd Quiets ]</i>

826
01:09:24,650 --> 01:09:25,020
<i>[ Sheriff ]
On the night of August 21,</i>

827
01:09:25,020 --> 01:09:27,650
<i>[ Sheriff ]
On the night of August 21,</i>

828
01:09:27,720 --> 01:09:31,590
<i>I was just leaving my office
to go home when Bob--</i>

829
01:09:31,660 --> 01:09:34,060
<i>Mr. Ewell came in.</i>

830
01:09:34,130 --> 01:09:36,220
<i>Very excited he was,</i>

831
01:09:36,300 --> 01:09:40,030
<i>and he said to get to his house
as quick as I could,</i>

832
01:09:40,100 --> 01:09:42,470
<i>that his girl
had been raped.</i>

833
01:09:42,540 --> 01:09:47,100
<i>I got in my car and went out
there as fast as I could.</i>

834
01:09:47,170 --> 01:09:50,140
<i>She was pretty well beat up.</i>

835
01:09:50,210 --> 01:09:54,010
<i>I asked her if Tom Robinson
beat her like that.</i>

836
01:09:54,080 --> 01:09:57,570
<i>She said, yes, he had.</i>

837
01:09:57,650 --> 01:10:00,980
<i>I asked if he'd
taken advantage of her.</i>

838
01:10:01,050 --> 01:10:04,080
<i>She said, "Yes, he did."</i>

839
01:10:04,160 --> 01:10:08,220
<i>That's all there was to it.</i>

840
01:10:08,290 --> 01:10:12,030
<i>[ Prosecutor ]
Thank you.</i>

841
01:10:12,100 --> 01:10:16,330
<i>[ Atticus ]
Did anybody call a doctor, Sheriff?</i>

842
01:10:16,400 --> 01:10:19,170
<i>- No, sir.
- Why not?</i>

843
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:21,500
<i>Well, I didn't think
it was necessary.</i>

844
01:10:21,570 --> 01:10:23,910
<i>She was pretty well beat up.</i>

845
01:10:23,980 --> 01:10:26,100
<i>Somethin' sure happened.
It was obvious.</i>

846
01:10:28,450 --> 01:10:33,580
<i>Now, Sheriff, you say that she was
mighty beat up. In what way?</i>

847
01:10:33,650 --> 01:10:36,520
<i>Well, she was beaten
around the head.</i>

848
01:10:36,590 --> 01:10:39,680
<i>There were bruises
already comin' on her arms.</i>

849
01:10:39,760 --> 01:10:42,890
<i>She had a black eye startin'.</i>

850
01:10:42,960 --> 01:10:45,830
<i>- Which eye?
- [ Sheriff ] Let's see.</i>

851
01:10:45,900 --> 01:10:48,490
<i>It was her left.</i>

852
01:10:48,570 --> 01:10:52,560
<i>Well, now, was that, uh--</i>

853
01:10:52,640 --> 01:10:55,370
<i>That was her left,
facing you...</i>

854
01:10:55,440 --> 01:10:57,430
<i>or looking the way
that you were?</i>

855
01:10:57,510 --> 01:11:02,850
<i>Oh, yes, that would make it
her right eye.</i>

856
01:11:02,920 --> 01:11:06,080
<i>It was her right eye, Mr. Finch.
Now I remember.</i>

857
01:11:06,150 --> 01:11:10,520
<i>She was beaten up
on that side of her face.</i>

858
01:11:12,090 --> 01:11:14,120
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

859
01:11:15,460 --> 01:11:17,950
<i>Which side again, Heck?</i>

860
01:11:18,030 --> 01:11:20,860
<i>The right side.</i>

861
01:11:20,930 --> 01:11:24,560
<i>She had bruises
on her arms and...</i>

862
01:11:24,640 --> 01:11:26,570
<i>she showed me her neck.</i>

863
01:11:26,640 --> 01:11:31,100
<i>There were definite finger marks
on her gullet.</i>

864
01:11:31,180 --> 01:11:33,110
<i>Well...</i>

865
01:11:33,180 --> 01:11:38,280
<i>all around her neck,
at the back of her throat?</i>

866
01:11:40,220 --> 01:11:42,240
<i>I'd say they were all around.</i>

867
01:11:50,660 --> 01:11:52,600
<i>[ Judge ]
The witness may be seated.</i>

868
01:11:54,200 --> 01:11:56,130
<i>[ Clerk ]
Robert E. Lee Ewell.</i>

869
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:59,330
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

870
01:12:00,910 --> 01:12:02,900
<i>Place your hand
on the Bible, please.</i>

871
01:12:02,980 --> 01:12:06,780
<i>Do you solemnly swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth, and nothing but
the truth, so help you God?</i>

872
01:12:06,850 --> 01:12:09,110
<i>- I do.
- Sit down, please.</i>

873
01:12:12,350 --> 01:12:14,290
<i>Now, Mr. Ewell,</i>

874
01:12:14,350 --> 01:12:17,380
<i>you tell us,
just in your own words,</i>

875
01:12:17,460 --> 01:12:20,220
<i>what happened on August 21.</i>

876
01:12:20,290 --> 01:12:22,230
<i>[ Ewell ]
Well, that night...</i>

877
01:12:22,290 --> 01:12:25,160
<i>I was comin' from the woods
with a load of kindlin'...</i>

878
01:12:25,230 --> 01:12:28,530
<i>and I heard Mayella screamin'
as I got to the fence.</i>

879
01:12:28,600 --> 01:12:33,200
<i>So I dropped my kindlin',
and I run as fast as I could,
but I run into the fence.</i>

880
01:12:33,270 --> 01:12:37,730
<i>But when I got loose,
I run up to the window,</i>

881
01:12:37,810 --> 01:12:40,400
<i>and I seen him
with my Mayella!</i>

882
01:12:40,480 --> 01:12:43,740
<i>- [ Crowd Murmuring ]
- [ Gavel Pounding ]</i>

883
01:12:43,820 --> 01:12:46,110
<i>[ Crowd Quiets ]</i>

884
01:12:46,190 --> 01:12:49,850
<i>What did you do
after you saw the defendant?</i>

885
01:12:49,920 --> 01:12:51,860
<i>I run around the house
tryin' to get in,</i>

886
01:12:51,920 --> 01:12:55,160
<i>but he done run through the front door
just ahead of me!</i>

887
01:12:55,230 --> 01:12:57,220
<i>But I seen who it was, all right!</i>

888
01:12:57,300 --> 01:13:02,700
<i>- I seen him.
- [ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

889
01:13:02,770 --> 01:13:06,470
<i>And I run in the house and...</i>

890
01:13:06,540 --> 01:13:10,770
<i>poor Mayella was layin'
on the floor squallin'.</i>

891
01:13:10,840 --> 01:13:14,240
<i>Then I run for Mr. Tate
just as quick as I could.</i>

892
01:13:14,310 --> 01:13:17,940
<i>Mm-hmm.
Thank you, Mr. Ewell.</i>

893
01:13:23,020 --> 01:13:27,520
<i>- [ Crowd Laughing ]
- [ Laughing ]</i>

894
01:13:27,590 --> 01:13:32,090
<i>Would you mind if I just,
uh, ask you a few questions, Mr. Ewell?</i>

895
01:13:32,160 --> 01:13:34,600
<i>No, sir, Mr. Finch,
I sure wouldn't.</i>

896
01:13:40,040 --> 01:13:42,630
<i>Folks were doin' a lot
of running that night.</i>

897
01:13:42,710 --> 01:13:47,480
<i>You say that you ran to the house,
you ran to the window,</i>

898
01:13:47,550 --> 01:13:52,040
<i>you ran inside, you ran to Mayella,
you ran to Sheriff Tate.</i>

899
01:13:52,120 --> 01:13:56,490
<i>Did you, during all this running,
run for a doctor?</i>

900
01:13:56,560 --> 01:13:59,390
<i>There wasn't no need to.
I seen who done it.</i>

901
01:14:01,930 --> 01:14:05,330
<i>Now, Mr. Ewell, you've heard
the sheriff's testimony.</i>

902
01:14:05,400 --> 01:14:07,660
<i>Do you agree with his description
of Mayella's injuries?</i>

903
01:14:07,730 --> 01:14:12,100
<i>I agree with everything
Mr. Tate said.</i>

904
01:14:12,170 --> 01:14:14,110
<i>Her eye was blacked.</i>

905
01:14:14,170 --> 01:14:17,800
<i>She was mighty beat up,
mighty beat up.</i>

906
01:14:20,080 --> 01:14:25,380
<i>Now, Mr. Ewell, can you, uh...
can you read and write?</i>

907
01:14:27,690 --> 01:14:31,550
<i>Yes, sir, Mr. Finch,
I can read and I can write.</i>

908
01:14:33,460 --> 01:14:35,720
<i>Good.</i>

909
01:14:35,790 --> 01:14:39,030
<i>- Then will you write your name, please.
- [ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

910
01:14:39,100 --> 01:14:42,290
<i>Write there.
Show us.</i>

911
01:15:13,630 --> 01:15:15,570
<i>So what's so interesting?</i>

912
01:15:15,630 --> 01:15:17,570
<i>You're left-handed, Mr. Ewell.</i>

913
01:15:17,640 --> 01:15:21,830
<i>What's that got to do with it, Judge?
I'm a God-fearin' man.</i>

914
01:15:21,910 --> 01:15:24,540
<i>That Atticus Finch,
he's tryin' to take advantage of me!</i>

915
01:15:24,610 --> 01:15:26,840
<i>You got to watch tricky lawyers
like Atticus Finch!</i>

916
01:15:26,910 --> 01:15:29,680
<i>Quiet. Quiet, sir.</i>

917
01:15:29,750 --> 01:15:32,680
<i>Now the witness
may take his seat.</i>

918
01:15:32,750 --> 01:15:37,950
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

919
01:15:42,790 --> 01:15:44,890
<i>[ Clerk ]
Mayella Violet Ewell.</i>

920
01:15:57,040 --> 01:16:00,640
<i>Put your hand
on the Bible, please.</i>

921
01:16:00,710 --> 01:16:02,650
<i>Do you solemnly swear
to tell the truth,</i>

922
01:16:02,710 --> 01:16:05,740
<i>the whole truth and nothing
but the truth, so help you God?</i>

923
01:16:05,820 --> 01:16:07,810
<i>Sit down, please.</i>

924
01:16:11,720 --> 01:16:14,190
<i>[ Prosecutor ]
Now, Mayella...</i>

925
01:16:15,560 --> 01:16:20,260
<i>suppose you tell us
just what happened, huh?</i>

926
01:16:20,330 --> 01:16:24,830
<i>Well, sir--
[ Clears Throat ]</i>

927
01:16:24,900 --> 01:16:29,340
<i>Sir... I was s-sittin'
on the porch...</i>

928
01:16:29,410 --> 01:16:32,340
<i>and he come along.</i>

929
01:16:34,410 --> 01:16:38,470
<i>There's this old chifforobe
in the yard,</i>

930
01:16:38,550 --> 01:16:42,010
<i>and l-I said,</i>

931
01:16:42,090 --> 01:16:44,750
<i>"You come in here, boy,
and bust up this chifforobe,</i>

932
01:16:44,820 --> 01:16:47,950
<i>and I'll give you a nickel."</i>

933
01:16:48,030 --> 01:16:50,620
<i>So he come on in the yard,</i>

934
01:16:50,700 --> 01:16:54,790
<i>and I go in the house
to get him the nickel...</i>

935
01:16:54,870 --> 01:16:58,300
<i>and I turn around
and before I know it, he's on me.</i>

936
01:17:00,040 --> 01:17:02,010
<i>I fought and hollered...</i>

937
01:17:02,070 --> 01:17:04,670
<i>but he had me
around the neck...</i>

938
01:17:04,740 --> 01:17:08,800
<i>and he hit me,
again and again.</i>

939
01:17:10,320 --> 01:17:15,510
<i>And the next thing I knew,
Papa was in the room...</i>

940
01:17:15,590 --> 01:17:21,290
<i>a-standin' over me, hollerin',
"Who done it? Who done it?"</i>

941
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:23,830
<i>Thank you, Mayella.</i>

942
01:17:25,400 --> 01:17:27,990
<i>Your witness, Atticus.</i>

943
01:17:31,240 --> 01:17:37,070
<i>Miss Mayella,
is your father good to you?</i>

944
01:17:37,140 --> 01:17:41,200
<i>I mean, is he easy
to get along with?</i>

945
01:17:42,510 --> 01:17:44,540
<i>Does tolerable.</i>

946
01:17:44,620 --> 01:17:46,950
<i>Except when he's drinking.</i>

947
01:17:49,250 --> 01:17:53,050
<i>When he's riled...
has he ever beaten you?</i>

948
01:17:59,060 --> 01:18:03,430
<i>My pa's never touched
a hair on my head in my life.</i>

949
01:18:07,870 --> 01:18:13,400
<i>You say that you asked Tom to come in
and chop up a-- What was it?</i>

950
01:18:14,510 --> 01:18:16,480
<i>A chifforobe.</i>

951
01:18:16,550 --> 01:18:21,820
<i>Was that the first time that you ever
asked him to come inside the fence?</i>

952
01:18:21,890 --> 01:18:25,080
<i>Yes.</i>

953
01:18:25,160 --> 01:18:30,490
<i>Didn't you ever ask him to come
inside the fence before?</i>

954
01:18:34,400 --> 01:18:36,830
<i>I might have.</i>

955
01:18:36,900 --> 01:18:39,840
<i>[ Atticus ]
Can you remember any other occasion?</i>

956
01:18:39,910 --> 01:18:42,530
<i>No.</i>

957
01:18:42,610 --> 01:18:48,270
<i>You say, "He caught me, he choked me,
and he took advantage of me."</i>

958
01:18:48,350 --> 01:18:50,280
<i>Is that right?</i>

959
01:18:54,390 --> 01:18:56,720
<i>Do you remember him
beating you about the face?</i>

960
01:18:58,560 --> 01:19:00,650
<i>No.</i>

961
01:19:00,730 --> 01:19:04,160
<i>I don't...
[ Clears Throat ]</i>

962
01:19:04,230 --> 01:19:06,990
<i>recollect if he hit me.</i>

963
01:19:10,670 --> 01:19:14,610
<i>I mean, y-yes!
H-He hit me!</i>

964
01:19:14,670 --> 01:19:17,340
<i>- He hit me!
- [ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

965
01:19:17,410 --> 01:19:21,680
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

966
01:19:21,750 --> 01:19:23,680
<i>Thank you.</i>

967
01:19:23,750 --> 01:19:26,510
<i>Now will you identify
the man who beat you.</i>

968
01:19:26,590 --> 01:19:29,850
<i>I most certainly will.
Sittin' right yonder.</i>

969
01:19:31,420 --> 01:19:34,860
<i>Tom, will you stand up, please?</i>

970
01:19:34,930 --> 01:19:38,760
<i>Let Miss Mayella
have a good long look at you.</i>

971
01:19:46,770 --> 01:19:50,730
<i>Tom, will you
catch this, please?</i>

972
01:19:54,310 --> 01:19:56,250
<i>Thank you.</i>

973
01:19:59,380 --> 01:20:03,410
<i>Now, then, this time, will you please
catch it with your left hand.</i>

974
01:20:03,490 --> 01:20:05,980
<i>I can't, sir.</i>

975
01:20:06,060 --> 01:20:07,990
<i>[ Atticus ]
Why can't you?</i>

976
01:20:08,060 --> 01:20:10,990
<i>I can't use
my left hand at all.</i>

977
01:20:11,060 --> 01:20:15,000
<i>I got it caught in a cotton gin
when I was 12 years old.</i>

978
01:20:15,070 --> 01:20:18,000
<i>All my muscles were tore loose.</i>

979
01:20:18,070 --> 01:20:23,170
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

980
01:20:23,240 --> 01:20:25,510
<i>[ Crowd Quiets ]</i>

981
01:20:34,590 --> 01:20:37,610
<i>Is this the man
who raped you?</i>

982
01:20:39,760 --> 01:20:42,520
<i>It most certainly is.</i>

983
01:20:42,590 --> 01:20:44,530
<i>[ Atticus ]
How?</i>

984
01:20:47,100 --> 01:20:51,090
<i>I don't know how.
He done it.</i>

985
01:20:51,170 --> 01:20:53,300
<i>[ Crying ]
He just done it.</i>

986
01:20:53,370 --> 01:20:56,140
<i>You have testified...</i>

987
01:20:56,210 --> 01:21:00,610
<i>that he choked you
and he beat you.</i>

988
01:21:00,680 --> 01:21:05,910
<i>You didn't say that he sneaked up
behind you and knocked you out cold,</i>

989
01:21:05,980 --> 01:21:09,980
<i>but that you turned around...</i>

990
01:21:10,060 --> 01:21:13,150
<i>and there he was.</i>

991
01:21:13,230 --> 01:21:17,320
<i>Do you want to tell us
what really happened?</i>

992
01:21:17,400 --> 01:21:19,330
<i>[ Gasps ]</i>

993
01:21:19,400 --> 01:21:23,330
<i>I got something to say...</i>

994
01:21:23,400 --> 01:21:27,000
<i>and then I ain't
gonna say no more!</i>

995
01:21:30,410 --> 01:21:33,670
<i>He took advantage of me!</i>

996
01:21:35,650 --> 01:21:41,180
<i>And if you fine,
fancy gentlemen...</i>

997
01:21:41,250 --> 01:21:43,350
<i>ain't gonna do
nothing about it,</i>

998
01:21:43,420 --> 01:21:48,690
<i>then you're just a bunch of lousy,
yellow, stinkin' cowards!</i>

999
01:21:48,760 --> 01:21:51,130
<i>The whole bunch of ya!</i>

1000
01:21:51,200 --> 01:21:54,460
<i>And your fancy airs
don't come to nothin'!</i>

1001
01:21:54,530 --> 01:21:57,470
<i>Your "ma'am"-ing
and your "Miss Mayella"-ing,</i>

1002
01:21:57,540 --> 01:22:00,800
<i>it don't come to nothin',
Mr. Finch!</i>

1003
01:22:00,870 --> 01:22:03,770
<i>N-N--
[ Gasps ]</i>

1004
01:22:03,840 --> 01:22:06,170
<i>- [ Crowd Murmuring ]
- [ Mayella Gasps ]</i>

1005
01:22:06,240 --> 01:22:08,680
<i>You sit down now.</i>

1006
01:22:08,750 --> 01:22:14,480
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

1007
01:22:18,060 --> 01:22:20,120
<i>[ Gavel Pounding ]</i>

1008
01:22:20,190 --> 01:22:22,920
<i>[ Crowd Quiets ]</i>

1009
01:22:24,630 --> 01:22:27,150
<i>Atticus.</i>

1010
01:22:29,730 --> 01:22:31,760
<i>Mr. Gilmer.</i>

1011
01:22:34,240 --> 01:22:36,170
<i>[ Clears Throat ]</i>

1012
01:22:36,240 --> 01:22:39,010
<i>The State rests, Judge.</i>

1013
01:22:46,420 --> 01:22:49,010
<i>[ Clerk ]
Tom Robinson, take the stand.</i>

1014
01:23:04,200 --> 01:23:06,330
<i>Put your hand on the Bible.</i>

1015
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:08,460
<i>Do you solemnly swear
to tell the truth,</i>

1016
01:23:08,540 --> 01:23:10,630
<i>the whole truth and nothing
but the truth, so help you God?</i>

1017
01:23:10,710 --> 01:23:12,800
<i>- I do.
- Sit down.</i>

1018
01:23:24,560 --> 01:23:27,150
<i>Now, Tom...</i>

1019
01:23:27,230 --> 01:23:30,660
<i>were you acquainted
with Mayella Violet Ewell?</i>

1020
01:23:30,730 --> 01:23:36,500
<i>Yes, sir. I had to pass her place
going to and from the field every day.</i>

1021
01:23:36,570 --> 01:23:40,660
<i>- Is there any other way to go?
- No, sir.</i>

1022
01:23:40,740 --> 01:23:43,000
<i>None's I know of.</i>

1023
01:23:43,070 --> 01:23:47,510
<i>- And did she ever speak to you?
- Why, yes, sir.</i>

1024
01:23:47,580 --> 01:23:50,610
<i>I'd tip my hat when I'd go by.</i>

1025
01:23:50,680 --> 01:23:54,780
<i>One day she asked me
to come inside the fence...</i>

1026
01:23:54,850 --> 01:23:57,950
<i>and bust up
a chifforobe for her.</i>

1027
01:23:58,020 --> 01:24:00,650
<i>She give me the hatchet,
and I broke it up.</i>

1028
01:24:00,730 --> 01:24:05,590
<i>And then she said, "l reckon I'll
have to give you a nickel, won't l?"</i>

1029
01:24:05,660 --> 01:24:08,790
<i>And I said, "No, ma'am.
There ain't no charge."</i>

1030
01:24:08,870 --> 01:24:12,300
<i>And I went home.</i>

1031
01:24:12,370 --> 01:24:17,100
<i>Mr. Finch, that was way last spring.
Way over a year ago.</i>

1032
01:24:17,180 --> 01:24:20,580
<i>Did you ever go
on the place again?</i>

1033
01:24:23,720 --> 01:24:26,150
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

1034
01:24:26,220 --> 01:24:28,150
<i>[ Atticus ]
When?</i>

1035
01:24:30,560 --> 01:24:33,990
<i>Well, I went lots of times.</i>

1036
01:24:34,060 --> 01:24:36,990
<i>Seemed like every time
I passed by yonder,</i>

1037
01:24:37,060 --> 01:24:39,500
<i>she would have
some little something for me to do:.</i>

1038
01:24:39,560 --> 01:24:42,400
<i>chopping kindlin'
and totin' water for her.</i>

1039
01:24:50,680 --> 01:24:52,770
<i>Tom...</i>

1040
01:24:52,840 --> 01:24:55,780
<i>what happened to you...</i>

1041
01:24:55,850 --> 01:25:00,110
<i>on the evening of August 21
of last year?</i>

1042
01:25:07,530 --> 01:25:13,290
<i>Mr. Finch, I was going home
as usual that evening.</i>

1043
01:25:15,200 --> 01:25:18,140
<i>When I passed the Ewell place,</i>

1044
01:25:18,200 --> 01:25:22,070
<i>Miss Mayella were on the porch,
like she said she were.</i>

1045
01:25:22,140 --> 01:25:26,470
<i>She said for me to come there
and help her a minute.</i>

1046
01:25:26,540 --> 01:25:28,810
<i>Well, I went inside the fence,</i>

1047
01:25:28,880 --> 01:25:32,650
<i>and I looked around
for some kindlin' to work on,</i>

1048
01:25:32,720 --> 01:25:34,740
<i>but I didn't see none.</i>

1049
01:25:36,720 --> 01:25:42,060
<i>Then she said to come in the house,
she has a door needs fixin'.</i>

1050
01:25:42,130 --> 01:25:46,060
<i>So I follows her inside,
and I looked at the door...</i>

1051
01:25:46,130 --> 01:25:49,830
<i>and it looked all right.</i>

1052
01:25:49,900 --> 01:25:51,930
<i>Then she shut the door.</i>

1053
01:25:54,010 --> 01:25:58,640
<i>All the time I was wondering
why it was so quiet.</i>

1054
01:26:00,180 --> 01:26:02,610
<i>Then it come to me.</i>

1055
01:26:02,680 --> 01:26:05,950
<i>There was not a child
on the place.</i>

1056
01:26:06,020 --> 01:26:11,220
<i>And I said, "Miss Mayella,
where are the children?"</i>

1057
01:26:11,290 --> 01:26:15,950
<i>She said,
"They all gone to get ice cream."</i>

1058
01:26:16,030 --> 01:26:21,090
<i>She said it took her a year to save
seven nickels, but she'd done it.</i>

1059
01:26:21,170 --> 01:26:24,470
<i>And they'd all gone to town.</i>

1060
01:26:24,540 --> 01:26:26,600
<i>What did you say then?</i>

1061
01:26:26,670 --> 01:26:32,130
<i>Well, I said something like...</i>

1062
01:26:32,210 --> 01:26:37,310
<i>"Why, Miss Mayella,
that's right nice of you to treat 'em."</i>

1063
01:26:37,380 --> 01:26:39,980
<i>She said, "You think so?"</i>

1064
01:26:40,050 --> 01:26:45,150
<i>Well, I said, "l best be goin'."
I couldn't do nothin' for her.</i>

1065
01:26:45,220 --> 01:26:47,820
<i>And she said I could.</i>

1066
01:26:47,890 --> 01:26:50,920
<i>I asked her what.</i>

1067
01:26:51,000 --> 01:26:55,430
<i>And she said to just step
on the chair yonder...</i>

1068
01:26:55,500 --> 01:27:00,440
<i>and get that box down
from on top of the chifforobe.</i>

1069
01:27:00,510 --> 01:27:04,440
<i>So I done like she told me,</i>

1070
01:27:04,510 --> 01:27:07,440
<i>and I was reachin'...</i>

1071
01:27:07,510 --> 01:27:12,810
<i>when the next thing I knows,
she grabbed me around the legs.</i>

1072
01:27:12,880 --> 01:27:16,820
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1073
01:27:19,520 --> 01:27:23,960
<i>She scared me so bad,
I hopped down and turned the chair over.</i>

1074
01:27:24,030 --> 01:27:26,620
<i>That was the only thing--</i>

1075
01:27:26,700 --> 01:27:29,460
<i>only furniture--
disturbed in the room, Mr. Finch,</i>

1076
01:27:29,530 --> 01:27:32,060
<i>I swear, when I left it.</i>

1077
01:27:34,910 --> 01:27:37,880
<i>And what happened after you
turned the chair over?</i>

1078
01:27:44,420 --> 01:27:46,380
<i>Tom?</i>

1079
01:27:52,120 --> 01:27:56,960
<i>You've sworn to tell the whole truth.
Will you do it?</i>

1080
01:28:00,270 --> 01:28:03,330
<i>What happened after that?</i>

1081
01:28:07,410 --> 01:28:10,570
<i>Mr. Finch,</i>

1082
01:28:10,640 --> 01:28:13,370
<i>I got down off the chair,</i>

1083
01:28:13,440 --> 01:28:16,710
<i>and I turned around...</i>

1084
01:28:16,780 --> 01:28:19,580
<i>and she sorta jumped on me.</i>

1085
01:28:20,720 --> 01:28:23,740
<i>She hugged me
around the waist.</i>

1086
01:28:23,820 --> 01:28:28,160
<i>She reached up and kissed me
on the face.</i>

1087
01:28:28,230 --> 01:28:33,030
<i>She said she'd never kissed
a grown man before...</i>

1088
01:28:33,100 --> 01:28:36,730
<i>and she might as well kiss me.</i>

1089
01:28:36,800 --> 01:28:40,900
<i>She says for me
to kiss her back,</i>

1090
01:28:40,970 --> 01:28:44,970
<i>and I said,
"Miss Mayella, let me outta here,"</i>

1091
01:28:45,040 --> 01:28:46,980
<i>and I tried to run.</i>

1092
01:28:48,810 --> 01:28:54,120
<i>Mr. Ewell cussed at her
from the window.</i>

1093
01:28:54,190 --> 01:28:56,280
<i>He said he's gonna kill her.</i>

1094
01:29:04,830 --> 01:29:06,760
<i>[ Atticus ]
And what happened after that?</i>

1095
01:29:10,400 --> 01:29:15,000
<i>I was runnin' so fast,
I don't know what happened.</i>

1096
01:29:23,150 --> 01:29:26,810
<i>Tom, did you rape
Mayella Ewell?</i>

1097
01:29:31,020 --> 01:29:34,220
<i>I did not, sir.</i>

1098
01:29:34,290 --> 01:29:37,850
<i>[ Atticus ]
Did you harm her in any way?</i>

1099
01:29:43,130 --> 01:29:47,260
<i>I did not, sir.</i>

1100
01:30:05,960 --> 01:30:09,320
<i>Robinson,</i>

1101
01:30:09,390 --> 01:30:13,830
<i>you're pretty good at bustin' up
chifforobes and kindlin'
with one hand, aren't ya?</i>

1102
01:30:13,900 --> 01:30:18,930
<i>Strong enough to choke the breath out
of a woman and sling her to the floor?</i>

1103
01:30:19,000 --> 01:30:24,410
<i>- I never done that, sir.
- But you're strong enough to.</i>

1104
01:30:24,480 --> 01:30:29,210
<i>- I reckon so, sir.
- Mm-hmm.</i>

1105
01:30:33,280 --> 01:30:37,950
<i>How come you so all fired anxious
to do that woman's chores?</i>

1106
01:30:40,660 --> 01:30:44,120
<i>Looks like she, she didn't
have nobody to help her.</i>

1107
01:30:44,200 --> 01:30:46,320
<i>Like I said, she--</i>

1108
01:30:46,400 --> 01:30:49,760
<i>With Mr. Ewell and seven children
on the place?</i>

1109
01:30:49,830 --> 01:30:53,860
<i>You did all this choppin' and work
out of sheer goodness, boy?</i>

1110
01:30:53,940 --> 01:30:57,900
<i>[ Chuckles ]
You're a mighty good fella, it seems.</i>

1111
01:30:57,980 --> 01:31:00,380
<i>Did all that
for not one penny?</i>

1112
01:31:01,750 --> 01:31:06,080
<i>Yes, sir.
I felt right sorry for her.</i>

1113
01:31:06,150 --> 01:31:08,910
<i>- She seemed--
- [ Gilmer Chuckling ]</i>

1114
01:31:24,040 --> 01:31:27,230
<i>You felt sorry for her?</i>

1115
01:31:27,310 --> 01:31:31,210
<i>A white woman?</i>

1116
01:31:31,280 --> 01:31:35,410
<i>You felt sorry for her?</i>

1117
01:31:44,390 --> 01:31:47,820
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1118
01:31:50,630 --> 01:31:53,650
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

1119
01:32:07,280 --> 01:32:09,910
<i>To begin with,</i>

1120
01:32:09,980 --> 01:32:12,610
<i>this case should never
have come to trial.</i>

1121
01:32:12,680 --> 01:32:15,780
<i>The State has not produced
one iota...</i>

1122
01:32:15,850 --> 01:32:17,840
<i>of medical evidence...</i>

1123
01:32:17,920 --> 01:32:21,650
<i>that the crime Tom Robinson
is charged with...</i>

1124
01:32:21,730 --> 01:32:25,160
<i>ever took place.</i>

1125
01:32:25,230 --> 01:32:27,560
<i>It has relied, instead,</i>

1126
01:32:27,630 --> 01:32:30,900
<i>upon the testimony
of two witnesses...</i>

1127
01:32:30,970 --> 01:32:34,340
<i>whose evidence has not only been
called into serious question...</i>

1128
01:32:34,410 --> 01:32:36,970
<i>on cross-examination,</i>

1129
01:32:37,040 --> 01:32:41,500
<i>but has been flatly contradicted
by the defendant.</i>

1130
01:32:43,210 --> 01:32:46,650
<i>There is circumstantial evidence
to indicate that...</i>

1131
01:32:46,720 --> 01:32:51,590
<i>Mayella Ewell
was beaten savagely...</i>

1132
01:32:51,660 --> 01:32:56,320
<i>by someone who led,
almost exclusively, with his left.</i>

1133
01:32:59,100 --> 01:33:03,160
<i>Tom Robinson now sits before you
having taken the oath...</i>

1134
01:33:03,230 --> 01:33:06,930
<i>with the only good hand
he possesses,</i>

1135
01:33:07,000 --> 01:33:09,630
<i>his right.</i>

1136
01:33:20,350 --> 01:33:25,080
<i>I have nothing but pity
in my heart...</i>

1137
01:33:25,160 --> 01:33:29,090
<i>for the chief witness
for the State.</i>

1138
01:33:31,260 --> 01:33:36,720
<i>She is the victim
of cruel poverty and ignorance.</i>

1139
01:33:40,370 --> 01:33:43,810
<i>But my pity...</i>

1140
01:33:43,870 --> 01:33:47,040
<i>does not extend so far...</i>

1141
01:33:47,110 --> 01:33:51,450
<i>as to her putting
a man's life at stake,</i>

1142
01:33:51,520 --> 01:33:56,980
<i>which she has done in an effort
to get rid of her own guilt.</i>

1143
01:33:57,050 --> 01:34:00,250
<i>Now I say "guilt," gentlemen,</i>

1144
01:34:00,320 --> 01:34:05,960
<i>because it was guilt
that motivated her.</i>

1145
01:34:07,160 --> 01:34:11,120
<i>She's committed no crime.</i>

1146
01:34:11,200 --> 01:34:14,100
<i>She has merely broken
a rigid and time-honored...</i>

1147
01:34:14,170 --> 01:34:17,870
<i>code of our society--</i>

1148
01:34:17,940 --> 01:34:22,280
<i>a code so severe that whoever breaks it
is hounded from our midst...</i>

1149
01:34:22,350 --> 01:34:24,540
<i>as unfit to live with.</i>

1150
01:34:24,620 --> 01:34:27,810
<i>She must destroy the evidence...</i>

1151
01:34:27,890 --> 01:34:30,580
<i>of her offense.</i>

1152
01:34:30,660 --> 01:34:35,290
<i>But what was the evidence
of her offense?</i>

1153
01:34:35,360 --> 01:34:39,420
<i>Tom Robinson, a human being.</i>

1154
01:34:41,870 --> 01:34:46,700
<i>She must put Tom Robinson
away from her.</i>

1155
01:34:48,240 --> 01:34:52,070
<i>Tom Robinson was to her
a daily reminder...</i>

1156
01:34:52,140 --> 01:34:54,940
<i>of what she did.</i>

1157
01:34:55,010 --> 01:34:58,350
<i>Now, what did she do?</i>

1158
01:34:58,420 --> 01:35:00,540
<i>She tempted a Negro.</i>

1159
01:35:00,620 --> 01:35:04,990
<i>She was white,
and she tempted a Negro.</i>

1160
01:35:05,060 --> 01:35:09,860
<i>She did something that,
in our society, is unspeakable.</i>

1161
01:35:09,930 --> 01:35:12,400
<i>She kissed a black man.</i>

1162
01:35:12,460 --> 01:35:16,730
<i>Not an old uncle,</i>

1163
01:35:16,800 --> 01:35:19,930
<i>but a strong, young Negro man.</i>

1164
01:35:22,970 --> 01:35:26,770
<i>No code mattered to her
before she broke it,</i>

1165
01:35:26,840 --> 01:35:31,040
<i>but it came crashing down
on her afterwards.</i>

1166
01:35:37,990 --> 01:35:42,190
<i>The witnesses for the State,
with the exception of the
sheriff of Maycomb County.</i>

1167
01:35:42,260 --> 01:35:45,630
<i>have presented themselves
to you gentlemen, to this court...</i>

1168
01:35:47,500 --> 01:35:51,590
<i>in the cynical confidence...</i>

1169
01:35:51,670 --> 01:35:55,630
<i>that their testimony
would not be doubted.</i>

1170
01:35:55,710 --> 01:36:00,700
<i>Confident that you gentlemen
would go along with them...</i>

1171
01:36:00,780 --> 01:36:04,440
<i>on the assumption--</i>

1172
01:36:04,520 --> 01:36:06,610
<i>the evil assumption--</i>

1173
01:36:06,680 --> 01:36:09,480
<i>that all Negroes lie,</i>

1174
01:36:09,550 --> 01:36:12,750
<i>all Negroes are basically
immoral beings,</i>

1175
01:36:12,820 --> 01:36:18,460
<i>all Negro men are not
to be trusted around our women.</i>

1176
01:36:20,430 --> 01:36:25,730
<i>An assumption that one associates
with minds of their caliber,</i>

1177
01:36:25,800 --> 01:36:30,570
<i>and which is, in itself,
gentlemen, a lie,</i>

1178
01:36:33,040 --> 01:36:37,100
<i>which I do not need
to point out to you.</i>

1179
01:36:42,550 --> 01:36:45,580
<i>And so,</i>

1180
01:36:45,660 --> 01:36:48,780
<i>a quiet, humble,
respectable Negro,</i>

1181
01:36:48,860 --> 01:36:52,990
<i>who has had the unmitigated
temerity...</i>

1182
01:36:53,060 --> 01:36:57,470
<i>to feel sorry
for a white woman,</i>

1183
01:36:57,540 --> 01:37:03,440
<i>has had to put his word
against two white people's.</i>

1184
01:37:07,880 --> 01:37:11,370
<i>The defendant is not guilty,</i>

1185
01:37:11,450 --> 01:37:15,820
<i>but somebody
in this courtroom is.</i>

1186
01:37:16,750 --> 01:37:19,920
<i>Now, gentlemen,</i>

1187
01:37:19,990 --> 01:37:22,050
<i>in this country,</i>

1188
01:37:22,130 --> 01:37:26,120
<i>our courts are the great levelers.</i>

1189
01:37:26,200 --> 01:37:28,530
<i>In our courts,</i>

1190
01:37:28,600 --> 01:37:34,040
<i>all men are created equal.</i>

1191
01:37:35,610 --> 01:37:39,570
<i>I'm no idealist
to believe firmly...</i>

1192
01:37:39,640 --> 01:37:42,870
<i>in the integrity of our courts
and of our jury system.</i>

1193
01:37:42,950 --> 01:37:47,850
<i>That's no ideal to me.
That is a living, working reality!</i>

1194
01:37:51,860 --> 01:37:57,390
<i>Now I am confident that you
gentlemen will review...</i>

1195
01:37:57,460 --> 01:38:00,660
<i>without passion...</i>

1196
01:38:00,730 --> 01:38:04,960
<i>the evidence
that you have heard,</i>

1197
01:38:05,040 --> 01:38:08,600
<i>come to a decision...</i>

1198
01:38:08,670 --> 01:38:11,870
<i>and restore this man
to his family.</i>

1199
01:38:21,290 --> 01:38:26,190
<i>In the name of God,</i>

1200
01:38:26,260 --> 01:38:29,990
<i>do your duty.</i>

1201
01:38:34,700 --> 01:38:36,960
<i>In the name of God,</i>

1202
01:38:37,030 --> 01:38:39,970
<i>believe...</i>

1203
01:38:40,040 --> 01:38:42,470
<i>Tom Robinson.</i>

1204
01:39:13,870 --> 01:39:17,170
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1205
01:39:17,240 --> 01:39:21,010
<i>How long has the jury
been out now, Reverend?</i>

1206
01:39:21,080 --> 01:39:23,380
<i>Well, let's see.</i>

1207
01:39:23,450 --> 01:39:26,680
<i>Almost two hours now.</i>

1208
01:39:26,750 --> 01:39:31,810
<i>I think that's
an awful good sign, don't you?</i>

1209
01:39:31,890 --> 01:39:33,860
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

1210
01:39:33,920 --> 01:39:37,860
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1211
01:40:18,270 --> 01:40:21,200
<i>Court's now in session.
Everybody rise.</i>

1212
01:40:40,690 --> 01:40:42,630
<i>Gentlemen of the jury,</i>

1213
01:40:42,690 --> 01:40:46,630
<i>- have you reached a verdict?
- [ Foreman ] We have, Your Honor.</i>

1214
01:40:51,370 --> 01:40:54,060
<i>Will the defendant please rise
and face the jury?</i>

1215
01:41:02,380 --> 01:41:04,440
<i>What is your verdict?</i>

1216
01:41:05,380 --> 01:41:07,410
<i>We find the defendant
guilty as charged.</i>

1217
01:41:07,480 --> 01:41:11,680
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1218
01:41:28,070 --> 01:41:31,840
<i>Gentlemen, this jury is dismissed.</i>

1219
01:41:31,910 --> 01:41:36,370
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1220
01:41:36,450 --> 01:41:39,040
<i>[ Clerk ]
Court is adjourned.</i>

1221
01:41:39,120 --> 01:41:41,380
<i>[ Murmuring Continues ]</i>

1222
01:41:41,450 --> 01:41:46,010
<i>[ Crowd Murmuring ]</i>

1223
01:41:49,630 --> 01:41:52,150
<i>I'll go to see Helen
first thing tomorrow morning.</i>

1224
01:41:52,230 --> 01:41:55,820
<i>I told her not to be disappointed,
we'd probably lose this one.</i>

1225
01:41:57,270 --> 01:41:59,700
<i>Tom.</i>

1226
01:42:14,220 --> 01:42:16,240
<i>Yes, Mr. Finch.</i>

1227
01:43:00,860 --> 01:43:03,590
<i>Miss Jean Louise.</i>

1228
01:43:03,670 --> 01:43:06,500
<i>Miss Jean Louise,
stand up.</i>

1229
01:43:10,440 --> 01:43:14,000
<i>Your father's passin'.</i>

1230
01:43:41,470 --> 01:43:44,240
<i>[ Maudie ]
Atticus?</i>

1231
01:43:48,050 --> 01:43:51,110
<i>I-I'm sorry, Atticus.</i>

1232
01:43:51,180 --> 01:43:54,310
<i>- Well, thank you, Maudie.
- [ Car Approaching ]</i>

1233
01:44:02,130 --> 01:44:05,530
<i>Atticus, can I see you
for a minute?</i>

1234
01:44:07,330 --> 01:44:09,960
<i>Will you excuse me?</i>

1235
01:44:34,090 --> 01:44:36,860
<i>Jem?</i>

1236
01:44:36,930 --> 01:44:39,400
<i>Yes'm.</i>

1237
01:44:42,330 --> 01:44:45,390
<i>I don't know if it'll help,</i>

1238
01:44:45,470 --> 01:44:47,940
<i>but I want to say this to you.</i>

1239
01:44:52,110 --> 01:44:56,010
<i>There's some men
in this world...</i>

1240
01:44:56,080 --> 01:45:00,210
<i>who are born to do
our unpleasant jobs for us.</i>

1241
01:45:03,990 --> 01:45:08,550
<i>Your father's one of them.</i>

1242
01:45:10,660 --> 01:45:12,930
<i>- Oh, well.
- [ Car Departing ]</i>

1243
01:45:37,090 --> 01:45:39,020
<i>What's the matter, Atticus?</i>

1244
01:45:43,490 --> 01:45:46,430
<i>Tom Robinson's dead.</i>

1245
01:45:55,840 --> 01:45:59,610
<i>They were taking him
to Abbottsville...</i>

1246
01:45:59,680 --> 01:46:02,240
<i>for safekeeping.</i>

1247
01:46:02,310 --> 01:46:06,270
<i>Tom broke loose and ran.</i>

1248
01:46:06,350 --> 01:46:11,980
<i>The deputy called out
to him to stop,</i>

1249
01:46:12,060 --> 01:46:15,620
<i>and Tom didn't stop.</i>

1250
01:46:15,690 --> 01:46:20,890
<i>He shot at him to wound him
and missed his aim.</i>

1251
01:46:23,800 --> 01:46:26,060
<i>Killed him.</i>

1252
01:46:30,370 --> 01:46:32,540
<i>The deputy says...</i>

1253
01:46:35,910 --> 01:46:40,580
<i>Tom just ran like a crazy man.</i>

1254
01:46:48,790 --> 01:46:54,390
<i>The last thing I told him was not to
lose heart, that we'd ask for an appeal.</i>

1255
01:47:02,710 --> 01:47:05,800
<i>We had such a good chance.</i>

1256
01:47:09,610 --> 01:47:13,410
<i>We had more than a good chance.</i>

1257
01:47:27,600 --> 01:47:31,060
<i>I have to go out
and tell his family.</i>

1258
01:47:31,130 --> 01:47:33,860
<i>You look after
the children, Maudie.</i>

1259
01:47:39,280 --> 01:47:42,110
<i>Atticus, you want me
to go with you?</i>

1260
01:47:42,180 --> 01:47:45,580
<i>No, son, I think I'd better
go out there alone.</i>

1261
01:47:45,650 --> 01:47:48,980
<i>Atticus.</i>

1262
01:47:49,050 --> 01:47:52,860
<i>I'm goin' with you.</i>

1263
01:47:52,940 --> 01:47:54,900
<i>All right, son.</i>

1264
01:48:04,350 --> 01:48:06,280
<i>[ Brakes Squeak ]</i>

1265
01:48:18,230 --> 01:48:22,630
<i>Hello, Mr. Finch.
I'm Spence, Tom's father.</i>

1266
01:48:22,700 --> 01:48:25,290
<i>Hello, Spence.</i>

1267
01:48:27,370 --> 01:48:30,070
<i>- Is Helen here?
- Yes, sir, she's inside lyin' down,</i>

1268
01:48:30,140 --> 01:48:32,070
<i>tryin' to get
a little sleep.</i>

1269
01:48:32,140 --> 01:48:34,670
<i>We been talkin'
about the appeal, Mr. Finch.</i>

1270
01:48:34,750 --> 01:48:37,610
<i>How long do you think it'll take?</i>

1271
01:48:39,120 --> 01:48:44,610
<i>Spence, there isn't
going to be any appeal.</i>

1272
01:48:45,960 --> 01:48:49,220
<i>Not now.
Tom is dead.</i>

1273
01:48:49,290 --> 01:48:51,230
<i>Dead?</i>

1274
01:48:57,800 --> 01:49:01,360
<i>[ Atticus ]
Helen.</i>

1275
01:49:01,440 --> 01:49:04,500
<i>[ Sobbing ]</i>

1276
01:49:08,310 --> 01:49:12,440
<i>[ Continues Sobbing ]</i>

1277
01:49:29,830 --> 01:49:33,200
<i>Boy.</i>

1278
01:49:33,270 --> 01:49:37,210
<i>Go inside and tell Atticus Finch
I said to come out here.</i>

1279
01:49:37,270 --> 01:49:39,900
<i>Go on, boy.</i>

1280
01:51:17,740 --> 01:51:22,370
<i>[ Adult Scout ] By October,
things had settled down again.</i>

1281
01:51:22,450 --> 01:51:28,210
<i>I still looked for Boo
every time I went by the Radley place.</i>

1282
01:51:30,250 --> 01:51:34,690
<i>This night my mind was filled
with Halloween.</i>

1283
01:51:34,760 --> 01:51:39,530
<i>There was to be a pageant representing
our county's agricultural products.</i>

1284
01:51:39,600 --> 01:51:43,190
<i>I was to be a ham.</i>

1285
01:51:43,270 --> 01:51:48,700
<i>Jem said he would escort me
to the school auditorium.</i>

1286
01:51:48,770 --> 01:51:53,640
<i>Thus began
our longest journey together.</i>

1287
01:52:11,400 --> 01:52:14,160
<i>- Scout!
- [ Scout ] Yeah?</i>

1288
01:52:14,230 --> 01:52:18,500
<i>Will you come on?
Everybody's gone.</i>

1289
01:52:18,570 --> 01:52:20,830
<i>I can't go home like this.</i>

1290
01:52:20,900 --> 01:52:23,340
<i>Well, I'm goin'.
It's almost 10:00...</i>

1291
01:52:23,410 --> 01:52:25,670
<i>and Atticus will be
waiting for us.</i>

1292
01:52:25,740 --> 01:52:28,840
<i>All right, I'm comin'.</i>

1293
01:52:28,910 --> 01:52:32,510
<i>But I feel like a fool
walkin' home like this.</i>

1294
01:52:32,580 --> 01:52:34,850
<i>It's not my fault
you lost your dress.</i>

1295
01:52:34,920 --> 01:52:38,010
<i>I didn't lose it.
Just can't find it.</i>

1296
01:52:38,090 --> 01:52:41,680
<i>- Where are your shoes?
- I can't find them either.</i>

1297
01:52:41,760 --> 01:52:44,350
<i>- You can get 'em tomorrow.
- But tomorrow's Sunday.</i>

1298
01:52:44,430 --> 01:52:47,860
<i>You can get the janitor
to let you in. Come on.</i>

1299
01:53:15,060 --> 01:53:18,990
<i>Here, Scout. Let me hold onto you
before you break your neck.</i>

1300
01:53:22,970 --> 01:53:25,830
<i>- Jem, you don't have to hold me.
- Shh.</i>

1301
01:53:27,740 --> 01:53:31,000
<i>- What's the matter?
- Hush a minute, Scout.</i>

1302
01:53:39,420 --> 01:53:41,850
<i>I thought I heard somethin'.</i>

1303
01:53:43,920 --> 01:53:46,120
<i>Ah... come on.</i>

1304
01:53:57,200 --> 01:53:59,960
<i>Wait.</i>

1305
01:54:00,040 --> 01:54:02,130
<i>- Jem, are you trying to scare me?
- Shh.</i>

1306
01:54:02,210 --> 01:54:05,270
<i>- You know I'm too old.
- Be quiet.</i>

1307
01:54:05,340 --> 01:54:09,640
<i>- [ Dog Howling ]
- I heard an old dog bayin'.</i>

1308
01:54:09,710 --> 01:54:12,810
<i>It's not that. I hear it
when we're walking along.</i>

1309
01:54:12,880 --> 01:54:16,480
<i>When we stop,
I don't hear it anymore.</i>

1310
01:54:16,550 --> 01:54:19,990
<i>Oh, yeah, my costume rustlin'.</i>

1311
01:54:20,060 --> 01:54:22,790
<i>Halloween's got ya.</i>

1312
01:54:22,860 --> 01:54:28,490
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

1313
01:54:28,570 --> 01:54:31,430
<i>I hear it now.</i>

1314
01:54:31,500 --> 01:54:34,990
<i>I'll bet it's just old Cecil Jacobs
tryin' to scare me.</i>

1315
01:54:35,070 --> 01:54:38,970
<i>Cecil Jacobs
is a big, wet hen!</i>

1316
01:54:42,750 --> 01:54:44,710
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

1317
01:54:46,080 --> 01:54:48,020
<i>[ Whispers ]
Come on.</i>

1318
01:54:50,750 --> 01:54:54,520
<i>[ Rustling ]</i>

1319
01:54:54,590 --> 01:55:00,120
<i>[ Rustling Continues ]</i>

1320
01:55:19,380 --> 01:55:21,110
<i>- [ Man Shouts ]
- [ Gasps ]</i>

1321
01:55:26,390 --> 01:55:28,320
<i>[ Both Grunting ]</i>

1322
01:55:28,390 --> 01:55:32,020
<i>Run, Scout!
Run, Scout! Run! Run!</i>

1323
01:55:36,070 --> 01:55:40,700
<i>- [ Footsteps, Man Grunting ]
- [ Jem Screams ]</i>

1324
01:55:41,910 --> 01:55:44,700
<i>- [ Jem Gasping ]
- [ Man Grunting ]</i>

1325
01:55:44,770 --> 01:55:49,940
<i>[ Continues Gasping ]</i>

1326
01:55:56,550 --> 01:56:01,220
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

1327
01:56:03,090 --> 01:56:05,120
<i>[ Screams ]</i>

1328
01:56:05,200 --> 01:56:10,130
<i>[ Men Grunting, Gasping ]</i>

1329
01:56:14,370 --> 01:56:18,310
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

1330
01:56:20,210 --> 01:56:25,150
<i>[ Grunting, Groaning ]</i>

1331
01:56:25,220 --> 01:56:27,150
<i>[ Fighting Stops ]</i>

1332
01:56:30,390 --> 01:56:32,320
<i>[ Body Falls ]</i>

1333
01:56:38,090 --> 01:56:43,000
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>

1334
01:56:43,070 --> 01:56:48,530
<i>[ Footsteps Passing ]</i>

1335
01:57:10,190 --> 01:57:12,130
<i>[ Door Creaks Open ]</i>

1336
01:57:20,200 --> 01:57:22,300
<i>Scout! Scout!</i>

1337
01:57:23,370 --> 01:57:25,470
<i>[ Crying ]</i>

1338
01:57:25,540 --> 01:57:27,480
<i>What happened?
What happened?</i>

1339
01:57:27,540 --> 01:57:29,980
<i>I don't know.
I just don't know.</i>

1340
01:57:31,380 --> 01:57:34,510
<i>- Cal, tell Dr. Reynolds to come over.
- Yes, sir.</i>

1341
01:57:36,390 --> 01:57:38,820
<i>- You all right?
- Yes, sir.</i>

1342
01:57:38,890 --> 01:57:41,320
<i>- Are you sure?
- Yes, sir.</i>

1343
01:57:47,100 --> 01:57:49,160
<i>[ Ringing ]</i>

1344
01:57:49,230 --> 01:57:51,760
<i>Sheriff Tate, please.</i>

1345
01:57:51,840 --> 01:57:54,600
<i>Atticus, is Jem dead?</i>

1346
01:57:54,670 --> 01:57:57,270
<i>No. He's unconscious.</i>

1347
01:57:57,340 --> 01:58:00,640
<i>We won't know how badly he's hurt
until the doctor gets here.</i>

1348
01:58:00,710 --> 01:58:03,270
<i>Heck? Atticus Finch.</i>

1349
01:58:03,350 --> 01:58:05,710
<i>Someone's been after my children.</i>

1350
01:58:08,690 --> 01:58:11,120
<i>He's got a bad break.</i>

1351
01:58:11,190 --> 01:58:14,450
<i>Like somebody tried
to wring his arm off.</i>

1352
01:58:20,460 --> 01:58:23,230
<i>I'll be right back, Atticus.</i>

1353
01:58:24,530 --> 01:58:26,470
<i>[ Sheriff ]
How's the boy, Doc?</i>

1354
01:58:26,540 --> 01:58:28,470
<i>He'll be all right.</i>

1355
01:58:30,710 --> 01:58:32,640
<i>Sheriff Tate.</i>

1356
01:58:41,720 --> 01:58:43,710
<i>[ Clears Throat ]</i>

1357
01:58:51,230 --> 01:58:53,160
<i>What is it, Heck?</i>

1358
01:58:58,070 --> 01:59:01,160
<i>Bob Ewell's lyin' on the ground
under that tree down yonder...</i>

1359
01:59:01,240 --> 01:59:04,730
<i>with a kitchen knife
stuck up under his ribs.</i>

1360
01:59:06,880 --> 01:59:08,810
<i>He's dead, Mr. Finch.</i>

1361
01:59:23,430 --> 01:59:26,690
<i>- Are you sure?
- [ Sheriff ] Yes, sir.</i>

1362
01:59:28,670 --> 01:59:33,190
<i>He's not gonna bother
these children anymore.</i>

1363
01:59:34,770 --> 01:59:37,500
<i>Miss Scout, you think you could
tell us what happened?</i>

1364
01:59:39,280 --> 01:59:41,370
<i>I don't know.</i>

1365
01:59:41,440 --> 01:59:43,710
<i>All of a sudden
somebody grabbed me,</i>

1366
01:59:43,780 --> 01:59:45,750
<i>knocked me down
on the ground.</i>

1367
01:59:45,820 --> 01:59:48,550
<i>Jem found me then.</i>

1368
01:59:48,620 --> 01:59:52,920
<i>Then Mr. Ewell, I reckon,
grabbed him again, and Jem hollered.</i>

1369
01:59:52,990 --> 01:59:57,390
<i>Then somebody grabbed me.
Mr. Ewell, I guess.</i>

1370
01:59:57,460 --> 02:00:00,620
<i>Somebody grabbed him...</i>

1371
02:00:00,700 --> 02:00:04,160
<i>and then I heard someone
pantin' and coughin'.</i>

1372
02:00:08,400 --> 02:00:10,570
<i>Then I saw someone
carrying Jem.</i>

1373
02:00:10,640 --> 02:00:12,840
<i>Well, who was it?</i>

1374
02:00:16,910 --> 02:00:19,070
<i>Why, there he is, Mr. Tate.</i>

1375
02:00:19,150 --> 02:00:22,880
<i>He can tell you his name.</i>

1376
02:00:49,110 --> 02:00:51,010
<i>Hey, Boo.</i>

1377
02:00:53,050 --> 02:00:57,650
<i>[ Atticus ] Miss Jean Louise,
Mr. Arthur Radley.</i>

1378
02:00:59,520 --> 02:01:02,460
<i>I believe he already knows you.</i>

1379
02:01:11,900 --> 02:01:14,340
<i>Heck, let's go out
on the front porch.</i>

1380
02:01:26,550 --> 02:01:30,680
<i>Would you like to say good night
to Jem, Mr. Arthur?</i>

1381
02:01:53,040 --> 02:01:56,810
<i>You can pet him, Mr. Arthur.
He's asleep.</i>

1382
02:01:56,880 --> 02:02:00,340
<i>You couldn't if he was awake, though.
He wouldn't let you.</i>

1383
02:02:04,220 --> 02:02:06,480
<i>Go ahead.</i>

1384
02:02:44,090 --> 02:02:47,190
<i>[ Scout ]
Let's go set in the swing, Mr. Arthur.</i>

1385
02:02:51,200 --> 02:02:54,140
<i>[ Atticus ]
Heck, l-l--</i>

1386
02:02:54,200 --> 02:02:59,470
<i>I guess that
the thing to do is, uh--</i>

1387
02:03:02,380 --> 02:03:07,150
<i>Good Lord...
I must be losin' my memory.</i>

1388
02:03:08,550 --> 02:03:14,150
<i>I can't remember
whether Jem is 12 or 13.</i>

1389
02:03:17,230 --> 02:03:22,990
<i>Anyway, it'll have to come
before the county court.</i>

1390
02:03:25,900 --> 02:03:29,840
<i>Of course, it's a clear-cut case
of self-defense.</i>

1391
02:03:29,910 --> 02:03:33,500
<i>I'll, uh-- Well, I'll run down
to the office--</i>

1392
02:03:33,580 --> 02:03:36,170
<i>Mr. Finch...</i>

1393
02:03:36,250 --> 02:03:38,840
<i>do you think Jem
killed Bob Ewell?</i>

1394
02:03:38,920 --> 02:03:42,180
<i>Is that what you think?</i>

1395
02:03:42,250 --> 02:03:45,520
<i>Your boy never stabbed him.</i>

1396
02:04:02,370 --> 02:04:05,970
<i>Bob Ewell fell on his knife.</i>

1397
02:04:06,040 --> 02:04:09,480
<i>He killed himself.</i>

1398
02:04:12,880 --> 02:04:15,820
<i>There's a black man
dead for no reason.</i>

1399
02:04:15,890 --> 02:04:19,820
<i>Now the man
responsible for it is dead.</i>

1400
02:04:19,890 --> 02:04:22,980
<i>Let the dead bury the dead
this time, Mr. Finch.</i>

1401
02:04:23,060 --> 02:04:25,490
<i>I never heard tell it was
against the law for any citizen...</i>

1402
02:04:25,560 --> 02:04:28,160
<i>to do his utmost to prevent a crime
from being committed,</i>

1403
02:04:28,230 --> 02:04:30,320
<i>which is exactly what he did.</i>

1404
02:04:30,400 --> 02:04:36,000
<i>But maybe you'll tell me
it's my duty to tell the town
all about it, not to hush it up.</i>

1405
02:04:36,070 --> 02:04:38,510
<i>You know what'll happen then.</i>

1406
02:04:38,570 --> 02:04:40,840
<i>All the ladies in Maycomb,
includin' my wife,</i>

1407
02:04:40,910 --> 02:04:45,350
<i>will be knockin' on his door
bringin' angel food cakes.</i>

1408
02:04:45,420 --> 02:04:48,680
<i>To my way of thinkin',
takin' one man,</i>

1409
02:04:48,750 --> 02:04:51,580
<i>who done you and this town
a big service,</i>

1410
02:04:51,650 --> 02:04:55,780
<i>and draggin' him with his shy ways
into the limelight--</i>

1411
02:04:55,860 --> 02:04:59,120
<i>To me, that's a sin.</i>

1412
02:04:59,200 --> 02:05:01,290
<i>It's a sin.</i>

1413
02:05:01,360 --> 02:05:05,300
<i>And I'm not about
to have it on my head.</i>

1414
02:05:05,370 --> 02:05:08,300
<i>I may not be much,
Mr. Finch,</i>

1415
02:05:08,370 --> 02:05:11,970
<i>but I'm still Sheriff
of Maycomb County,</i>

1416
02:05:12,040 --> 02:05:16,140
<i>and Bob Ewell fell on his knife.</i>

1417
02:05:16,210 --> 02:05:18,150
<i>Good night, sir.</i>

1418
02:05:23,550 --> 02:05:27,990
<i>[ Car Door Shuts, Engine Starts ]</i>

1419
02:05:57,350 --> 02:05:59,950
<i>Mr. Tate was right.</i>

1420
02:06:04,030 --> 02:06:06,620
<i>What do you mean?</i>

1421
02:06:06,700 --> 02:06:10,460
<i>Well...
it would be...</i>

1422
02:06:10,530 --> 02:06:14,800
<i>sort of like shooting
a mockingbird, wouldn't it?</i>

1423
02:06:42,900 --> 02:06:44,990
<i>Thank you, Arthur.</i>

1424
02:06:52,840 --> 02:06:55,780
<i>Thank you for my children.</i>

1425
02:07:10,030 --> 02:07:13,290
<i>[ Adult Scout ]
Neighbors bring food with death...</i>

1426
02:07:13,360 --> 02:07:15,460
<i>and flowers with sickness...</i>

1427
02:07:15,530 --> 02:07:19,130
<i>and little things in between.</i>

1428
02:07:19,200 --> 02:07:21,970
<i>Boo was our neighbor.</i>

1429
02:07:22,040 --> 02:07:24,800
<i>He gave us two soap dolls,</i>

1430
02:07:24,870 --> 02:07:27,640
<i>a broken watch and chain,</i>

1431
02:07:27,710 --> 02:07:29,970
<i>a knife...</i>

1432
02:07:30,050 --> 02:07:32,480
<i>and our lives.</i>

1433
02:07:37,390 --> 02:07:40,320
<i>One time Atticus said...</i>

1434
02:07:40,390 --> 02:07:45,830
<i>you never really knew a man
until you stood in his shoes
and walked around in them.</i>

1435
02:07:50,400 --> 02:07:54,600
<i>Just standing
on the Radley porch was enough.</i>

1436
02:08:01,180 --> 02:08:04,940
<i>The summer that had begun
so long ago had ended,</i>

1437
02:08:05,010 --> 02:08:07,450
<i>and another summer
had taken its place.</i>

1438
02:08:07,520 --> 02:08:09,450
<i>And a fall.</i>

1439
02:08:09,520 --> 02:08:12,950
<i>And Boo Radley had come out.</i>

1440
02:08:16,190 --> 02:08:19,630
<i>I was to think
of these days many times,</i>

1441
02:08:19,700 --> 02:08:21,790
<i>of Jem and Dill...</i>

1442
02:08:21,860 --> 02:08:25,130
<i>and Boo Radley
and Tom Robinson.</i>

1443
02:08:26,870 --> 02:08:29,130
<i>And Atticus.</i>

1444
02:08:36,880 --> 02:08:40,980
<i>He would be
in Jem's room all night,</i>

1445
02:08:41,050 --> 02:08:45,990
<i>and he would be there when Jem
waked up in the morning.</i>


